246 /**
247  * \brief Create the path if default-rule-path was specified
248  * \param sig_file The name of the file
249  * \retval str Pointer to the string path + sig_file
250  */
251 char *DetectLoadCompleteSigPath(const DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx, char *sig_file)
252 {
253  char *defaultpath = NULL;
254  char *path = NULL;
255  char varname[128] = "default-rule-path";
256 
257  if (strlen(de_ctx->config_prefix) > 0) {
258  snprintf(varname, sizeof(varname), "%s.default-rule-path",
259  de_ctx->config_prefix);
260  }
261 
262  /* Path not specified */
263  if (PathIsRelative(sig_file)) {
264  if (ConfGet(varname, &defaultpath) == 1) {
265  SCLogDebug("Default path: %s", defaultpath);
266  size_t path_len = sizeof(char) * (strlen(defaultpath) +
267  strlen(sig_file) + 2);
268  path = SCMalloc(path_len);
269  if (unlikely(path == NULL))
270  return NULL;
271  strlcpy(path, defaultpath, path_len);
272 #if defined OS_WIN32 || defined __CYGWIN__
273  if (path[strlen(path) - 1] != '\\')
274  strlcat(path, "\\\\", path_len);
275 #else
276  if (path[strlen(path) - 1] != '/')
277  strlcat(path, "/", path_len);
278 #endif
279  strlcat(path, sig_file, path_len);
280  } else {
281  path = SCStrdup(sig_file);
282  if (unlikely(path == NULL))
283  return NULL;
284  }
285  } else {
286  path = SCStrdup(sig_file);
287  if (unlikely(path == NULL))
288  return NULL;
289  }
290  return path;
291 }
292 
293 /**
294  * \brief Load a file with signatures
295  * \param de_ctx Pointer to the detection engine context
296  * \param sig_file Filename to load signatures from
297  * \param goodsigs_tot Will store number of valid signatures in the file
298  * \param badsigs_tot Will store number of invalid signatures in the file
299  * \retval 0 on success, -1 on error
300  */
301 static int DetectLoadSigFile(DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx, char *sig_file,
302  int *goodsigs, int *badsigs)
303 {
304  Signature *sig = NULL;
305  int good = 0, bad = 0;
306  char line[DETECT_MAX_RULE_SIZE] = "";
307  size_t offset = 0;
308  int lineno = 0, multiline = 0;
309 
310  (*goodsigs) = 0;
311  (*badsigs) = 0;
312 
313  FILE *fp = fopen(sig_file, "r");
314  if (fp == NULL) {
315  SCLogError(SC_ERR_OPENING_RULE_FILE, "opening rule file %s:"
316  " %s.", sig_file, strerror(errno));
317  return -1;
318  }
319 
320  while(fgets(line + offset, (int)sizeof(line) - offset, fp) != NULL) {
321  lineno++;
322  size_t len = strlen(line);
323 
324  /* ignore comments and empty lines */
325  if (line[0] == '\n' || line [0] == '\r' || line[0] == ' ' || line[0] == '#' || line[0] == '\t')
326  continue;
327 
328  /* Check for multiline rules. */
329  while (len > 0 && isspace((unsigned char)line[--len]));
330  if (line[len] == '\\') {
331  multiline++;
332  offset = len;
333  if (offset < sizeof(line) - 1) {
334  /* We have room for more. */
335  continue;
336  }
337  /* No more room in line buffer, continue, rule will fail
338  * to parse. */
339  }
340 
341  /* Check if we have a trailing newline, and remove it */
342  len = strlen(line);
343  if (len > 0 && (line[len - 1] == '\n' || line[len - 1] == '\r')) {
344  line[len - 1] = '\0';
345  }
346 
347  /* Reset offset. */
348  offset = 0;
349 
350  de_ctx->rule_file = sig_file;
351  de_ctx->rule_line = lineno - multiline;
352 
353  sig = DetectEngineAppendSig(de_ctx, line);
354  if (sig != NULL) {
355  if (rule_engine_analysis_set || fp_engine_analysis_set) {
356  sig->mpm_sm = RetrieveFPForSigV2(sig);
357  if (fp_engine_analysis_set) {
358  EngineAnalysisFP(sig, line);
359  }
360  if (rule_engine_analysis_set) {
361  EngineAnalysisRules(sig, line);
362  }
363  }
364  SCLogDebug("signature %"PRIu32" loaded", sig->id);
365  good++;
366  } else {
367  SCLogError(SC_ERR_INVALID_SIGNATURE, "error parsing signature \"%s\" from "
368  "file %s at line %"PRId32"", line, sig_file, lineno - multiline);
369 
370  if (rule_engine_analysis_set) {
371  EngineAnalysisRulesFailure(line, sig_file, lineno - multiline);
372  }
373  bad++;
374  }
375  multiline = 0;
376  }
377  fclose(fp);
378 
379  *goodsigs = good;
380  *badsigs = bad;
381  return 0;
382 }
383 
384 /**
385  * \brief Expands wildcards and reads signatures from each matching file
386  * \param de_ctx Pointer to the detection engine context
387  * \param sig_file Filename (or pattern) holding signatures
388  * \retval -1 on error
389  */
390 static int ProcessSigFiles(DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx, char *pattern,
391  SigFileLoaderStat *st, int *good_sigs, int *bad_sigs)
392 {
393  if (pattern == NULL) {
394  SCLogError(SC_ERR_INVALID_ARGUMENT, "opening rule file null");
395  return -1;
396  }
397 
398  glob_t files;
399  int r = glob(pattern, 0, NULL, &files);
400 
401  if (r == GLOB_NOMATCH) {
402  SCLogWarning(SC_ERR_NO_RULES, "No rule files match the pattern %s", pattern);
403  ++(st->bad_files);
404  ++(st->total_files);
405  return -1;
406  } else if (r != 0) {
407  SCLogError(SC_ERR_OPENING_RULE_FILE, "error expanding template %s: %s",
408  pattern, strerror(errno));
409  return -1;
410  }
411 
412  for (size_t i = 0; i < (size_t)files.gl_pathc; i++) {
413  char *fname = files.gl_pathv[i];
414  SCLogInfo("Loading rule file: %s", fname);
415  r = DetectLoadSigFile(de_ctx, fname, good_sigs, bad_sigs);
416  if (r < 0) {
417  ++(st->bad_files);
418  }
419 
420  ++(st->total_files);
421 
422  if (*good_sigs == 0) {
423  SCLogWarning(SC_ERR_NO_RULES,
424  "No rules loaded from %s", fname);
425  }
426 
427  st->good_sigs_total += *good_sigs;
428  st->bad_sigs_total += *bad_sigs;
429  }
430 
431  globfree(&files);
432  return r;
433 }
434 
435 /**
436  * \brief Load signatures
437  * \param de_ctx Pointer to the detection engine context
438  * \param sig_file Filename (or pattern) holding signatures
439  * \param sig_file_exclusive File passed in 'sig_file' should be loaded exclusively.
440  * \retval -1 on error
441  */
442 int SigLoadSignatures(DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx, char *sig_file, int sig_file_exclusive)
443 {
444  SCEnter();
445 
446  ConfNode *rule_files;
447  ConfNode *file = NULL;
448  SigFileLoaderStat sig_stat;
449  int ret = 0;
450  char *sfile = NULL;
451  char varname[128] = "rule-files";
452  int good_sigs = 0;
453  int bad_sigs = 0;
454 
455  memset(&sig_stat, 0, sizeof(SigFileLoaderStat));
456 
457  if (strlen(de_ctx->config_prefix) > 0) {
458  snprintf(varname, sizeof(varname), "%s.rule-files",
459  de_ctx->config_prefix);
460  }
461 
462  if (RunmodeGetCurrent() == RUNMODE_ENGINE_ANALYSIS) {
463  fp_engine_analysis_set = SetupFPAnalyzer();
464  rule_engine_analysis_set = SetupRuleAnalyzer();
465  }
466 
467  /* ok, let's load signature files from the general config */
468  if (!(sig_file != NULL && sig_file_exclusive == TRUE)) {
469  rule_files = ConfGetNode(varname);
470  if (rule_files != NULL) {
471  if (!ConfNodeIsSequence(rule_files)) {
472  SCLogWarning(SC_ERR_INVALID_ARGUMENT,
473  "Invalid rule-files configuration section: "
474  "expected a list of filenames.");
475  }
476  else {
477  TAILQ_FOREACH(file, &rule_files->head, next) {
478  sfile = DetectLoadCompleteSigPath(de_ctx, file->val);
479  good_sigs = bad_sigs = 0;
480  ret = ProcessSigFiles(de_ctx, sfile, &sig_stat, &good_sigs, &bad_sigs);
481  SCFree(sfile);
482 
483  if (ret != 0 || good_sigs == 0) {
484  if (de_ctx->failure_fatal == 1) {
485  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
486  }
487  }
488  }
489  }
490  }
491  }
492 
493  /* If a Signature file is specified from commandline, parse it too */
494  if (sig_file != NULL) {
495  ret = ProcessSigFiles(de_ctx, sig_file, &sig_stat, &good_sigs, &bad_sigs);
496 
497  if (ret != 0) {
498  if (de_ctx->failure_fatal == 1) {
499  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
500  }
501  }
502 
503  if (good_sigs == 0) {
504  SCLogError(SC_ERR_NO_RULES, "No rules loaded from %s", sig_file);
505 
506  if (de_ctx->failure_fatal == 1) {
507  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
508  }
509  }
510  }
511 
512  /* now we should have signatures to work with */
513  if (sig_stat.good_sigs_total <= 0) {
514  if (sig_stat.total_files > 0) {
515  SCLogWarning(SC_ERR_NO_RULES_LOADED, "%d rule files specified, but no rule was loaded at all!", sig_stat.total_files);
516  } else {
517  SCLogInfo("No signatures supplied.");
518  goto end;
519  }
520  } else {
521  /* we report the total of files and rules successfully loaded and failed */
522  SCLogInfo("%" PRId32 " rule files processed. %" PRId32 " rules successfully loaded, %" PRId32 " rules failed",
523  sig_stat.total_files, sig_stat.good_sigs_total, sig_stat.bad_sigs_total);
524  }
525 
526  if ((sig_stat.bad_sigs_total || sig_stat.bad_files) && de_ctx->failure_fatal) {
527  ret = -1;
528  goto end;
529  }
530 
531  SCSigRegisterSignatureOrderingFuncs(de_ctx);
532  SCSigOrderSignatures(de_ctx);
533  SCSigSignatureOrderingModuleCleanup(de_ctx);
534 
535  /* Setup the signature group lookup structure and pattern matchers */
536  if (SigGroupBuild(de_ctx) < 0)
537  goto end;
538 
539  ret = 0;
540 
541  end:
542  if (RunmodeGetCurrent() == RUNMODE_ENGINE_ANALYSIS) {
543  if (rule_engine_analysis_set) {
544  CleanupRuleAnalyzer();
545  }
546  if (fp_engine_analysis_set) {
547  CleanupFPAnalyzer();
548  }
549  }
550 
551  DetectParseDupSigHashFree(de_ctx);
552  SCReturnInt(ret);
553 }
554 
555 int SigMatchSignaturesRunPostMatch(ThreadVars *tv,
556  DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx, DetectEngineThreadCtx *det_ctx, Packet *p,
557  Signature *s)
558 {
559  /* run the packet match functions */
560  if (s->sm_arrays[DETECT_SM_LIST_POSTMATCH] != NULL) {
561  KEYWORD_PROFILING_SET_LIST(det_ctx, DETECT_SM_LIST_POSTMATCH);
562 
563  SigMatchData *smd = s->sm_arrays[DETECT_SM_LIST_POSTMATCH];
564  SCLogDebug("running match functions, sm %p", smd);
565 
566  if (smd != NULL) {
567  while (1) {
568  KEYWORD_PROFILING_START;
569  (void)sigmatch_table[smd->type].Match(tv, det_ctx, p, s, smd->ctx);
570  KEYWORD_PROFILING_END(det_ctx, smd->type, 1);
571  if (smd->is_last)
572  break;
573  smd++;
574  }
575  }
576  }
577 
578  DetectReplaceExecute(p, det_ctx);
579 
580  if (s->flags & SIG_FLAG_FILESTORE)
581  DetectFilestorePostMatch(tv, det_ctx, p, s);
582 
583  return 1;
584 }
585 
586 /**
587  * \brief Get the SigGroupHead for a packet.
588  *
589  * \param de_ctx detection engine context
590  * \param det_ctx thread detection engine content
591  * \param p packet
592  *
593  * \retval sgh the SigGroupHead or NULL if non applies to the packet
594  */
595 SigGroupHead *SigMatchSignaturesGetSgh(DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx, DetectEngineThreadCtx *det_ctx, Packet *p)
596 {
597  SCEnter();
598 
599  int f;
600  SigGroupHead *sgh = NULL;
601 
602  /* if the packet proto is 0 (not set), we're inspecting it against
603  * the decoder events sgh we have. */
604  if (p->proto == 0 && p->events.cnt > 0) {
605  SCReturnPtr(de_ctx->decoder_event_sgh, "SigGroupHead");
606  }
607 
608  /* select the flow_gh */
609  if (p->flowflags & FLOW_PKT_TOCLIENT)
610  f = 0;
611  else
612  f = 1;
613 
614  SCLogDebug("f %d", f);
615  SCLogDebug("IP_GET_IPPROTO(p) %u", IP_GET_IPPROTO(p));
616 
617  /* find the right mpm instance */
618  DetectAddress *ag = DetectAddressLookupInHead(de_ctx->flow_gh[f].src_gh[IP_GET_IPPROTO(p)], &p->src);
619  if (ag != NULL) {
620  /* source group found, lets try a dst group */
621  ag = DetectAddressLookupInHead(ag->dst_gh, &p->dst);
622  if (ag != NULL) {
623  if (ag->port == NULL) {
624  SCLogDebug("we don't have ports");
625  sgh = ag->sh;
626  } else {
627  SCLogDebug("we have ports");
628 
629  DetectPort *sport = DetectPortLookupGroup(ag->port,p->sp);
630  if (sport != NULL) {
631  DetectPort *dport = DetectPortLookupGroup(sport->dst_ph,p->dp);
632  if (dport != NULL) {
633  sgh = dport->sh;
634  } else {
635  SCLogDebug("no dst port group found for the packet with dp %"PRIu16"", p->dp);
636  }
637  } else {
638  SCLogDebug("no src port group found for the packet with sp %"PRIu16"", p->sp);
639  }
640  }
641  } else {
642  SCLogDebug("no dst address group found for the packet");
643  }
644  } else {
645  SCLogDebug("no src address group found for the packet");
646  }
647 
648  SCReturnPtr(sgh, "SigGroupHead");
649 }
650 
651 /** \brief Get the smsgs relevant to this packet
652  *
653  * \param f LOCKED flow
654  * \param p packet
655  * \param flags stream flags
656  */
657 static StreamMsg *SigMatchSignaturesGetSmsg(Flow *f, Packet *p, uint8_t flags)
658 {
659  SCEnter();
660 
661  DEBUG_ASSERT_FLOW_LOCKED(f);
662 
663  StreamMsg *smsg = NULL;
664 
665  if (p->proto == IPPROTO_TCP && f->protoctx != NULL && (p->flags & PKT_STREAM_EST)) {
666  TcpSession *ssn = (TcpSession *)f->protoctx;
667 
668  /* at stream eof, or in inline mode, inspect all smsg's */
669  if ((flags & STREAM_EOF) || StreamTcpInlineMode()) {
670  if (p->flowflags & FLOW_PKT_TOSERVER) {
671  smsg = ssn->toserver_smsg_head;
672  /* deref from the ssn */
673  ssn->toserver_smsg_head = NULL;
674  ssn->toserver_smsg_tail = NULL;
675 
676  SCLogDebug("to_server smsg %p at stream eof", smsg);
677  } else {
678  smsg = ssn->toclient_smsg_head;
679  /* deref from the ssn */
680  ssn->toclient_smsg_head = NULL;
681  ssn->toclient_smsg_tail = NULL;
682 
683  SCLogDebug("to_client smsg %p at stream eof", smsg);
684  }
685  } else {
686  if (p->flowflags & FLOW_PKT_TOSERVER) {
687  StreamMsg *head = ssn->toserver_smsg_head;
688  if (unlikely(head == NULL)) {
689  SCLogDebug("no smsgs in to_server direction");
690  goto end;
691  }
692 
693  /* if the smsg is bigger than the current packet, we will
694  * process the smsg in a later run */
695  if (SEQ_GT((head->seq + head->data_len), (TCP_GET_SEQ(p) + p->payload_len))) {
696  SCLogDebug("smsg ends beyond current packet, skipping for now %"PRIu32">%"PRIu32,
697  (head->seq + head->data_len), (TCP_GET_SEQ(p) + p->payload_len));
698  goto end;
699  }
700 
701  smsg = head;
702  /* deref from the ssn */
703  ssn->toserver_smsg_head = NULL;
704  ssn->toserver_smsg_tail = NULL;
705 
706  SCLogDebug("to_server smsg %p", smsg);
707  } else {
708  StreamMsg *head = ssn->toclient_smsg_head;
709  if (unlikely(head == NULL))
710  goto end;
711 
712  /* if the smsg is bigger than the current packet, we will
713  * process the smsg in a later run */
714  if (SEQ_GT((head->seq + head->data_len), (TCP_GET_SEQ(p) + p->payload_len))) {
715  SCLogDebug("smsg ends beyond current packet, skipping for now %"PRIu32">%"PRIu32,
716  (head->seq + head->data_len), (TCP_GET_SEQ(p) + p->payload_len));
717  goto end;
718  }
719 
720  smsg = head;
721  /* deref from the ssn */
722  ssn->toclient_smsg_head = NULL;
723  ssn->toclient_smsg_tail = NULL;
724 
725  SCLogDebug("to_client smsg %p", smsg);
726  }
727  }
728  }
729 
730 end:
731  SCReturnPtr(smsg, "StreamMsg");
732 }
733 
734 static inline void DetectPrefilterMergeSort(DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx,
735  DetectEngineThreadCtx *det_ctx)
736 // SigGroupHead *sgh)
737 {
738  SigIntId mpm, nonmpm;
739  det_ctx->match_array_cnt = 0;
740  SigIntId *mpm_ptr = det_ctx->pmq.rule_id_array;
741  SigIntId *nonmpm_ptr = det_ctx->non_mpm_id_array;
742  //SigIntId *nonmpm_ptr = sgh->non_mpm_id_array;
743  uint32_t m_cnt = det_ctx->pmq.rule_id_array_cnt;
744  //uint32_t n_cnt = sgh->non_mpm_id_cnt;
745  uint32_t n_cnt = det_ctx->non_mpm_id_cnt;
746  SCLogDebug("PMQ rule id array count %d", det_ctx->pmq.rule_id_array_cnt);
747 // SCLogDebug("SGH non-MPM id count %d", sgh->non_mpm_id_cnt);
748  SigIntId *final_ptr;
749  uint32_t final_cnt;
750  SigIntId id;
751  SigIntId previous_id = (SigIntId)-1;
752  Signature **sig_array = de_ctx->sig_array;
753  Signature **match_array = det_ctx->match_array;
754  Signature *s;
755 
756  /* Load first values. */
757  if (likely(m_cnt)) {
758  mpm = *mpm_ptr;
759  } else {
760  /* mpm list is empty */
761  final_ptr = nonmpm_ptr;
762  final_cnt = n_cnt;
763  goto final;
764  }
765  if (likely(n_cnt)) {
766  nonmpm = *nonmpm_ptr;
767  } else {
768  /* non-mpm list is empty. */
769  final_ptr = mpm_ptr;
770  final_cnt = m_cnt;
771  goto final;
772  }
773  while (1) {
774  if (mpm <= nonmpm) {
775  /* Take from mpm list */
776  id = mpm;
777 
778  s = sig_array[id];
779  /* As the mpm list can contain duplicates, check for that here. */
780  if (likely(id != previous_id)) {
781  *match_array++ = s;
782  previous_id = id;
783  }
784  if (unlikely(--m_cnt == 0)) {
785  /* mpm list is now empty */
786  final_ptr = nonmpm_ptr;
787  final_cnt = n_cnt;
788  goto final;
789  }
790  mpm_ptr++;
791  mpm = *mpm_ptr;
792  } else {
793  id = nonmpm;
794 
795  s = sig_array[id];
796  /* As the mpm list can contain duplicates, check for that here. */
797  if (likely(id != previous_id)) {
798  *match_array++ = s;
799  previous_id = id;
800  }
801  if (unlikely(--n_cnt == 0)) {
802  final_ptr = mpm_ptr;
803  final_cnt = m_cnt;
804  goto final;
805  }
806  nonmpm_ptr++;
807  nonmpm = *nonmpm_ptr;
808  }
809  }
810 
811  final: /* Only one list remaining. Just walk that list. */
812 
813  while (final_cnt-- > 0) {
814  id = *final_ptr++;
815  s = sig_array[id];
816 
817  /* As the mpm list can contain duplicates, check for that here. */
818  if (likely(id != previous_id)) {
819  *match_array++ = s;
820  previous_id = id;
821  }
822  }
823 
824  det_ctx->match_array_cnt = match_array - det_ctx->match_array;
825 
826  BUG_ON((det_ctx->pmq.rule_id_array_cnt + det_ctx->non_mpm_id_cnt) < det_ctx->match_array_cnt);
827 }
828 
829 /* Return true is the list is sorted smallest to largest */
830 static void QuickSortSigIntId(SigIntId *sids, uint32_t n)
831 {
832  if (n < 2)
833  return;
834  SigIntId p = sids[n / 2];
835  SigIntId *l = sids;
836  SigIntId *r = sids + n - 1;
837  while (l <= r) {
838  if (*l < p)
839  l++;
840  else if (*r > p)
841  r--;
842  else {
843  SigIntId t = *l;
844  *l = *r;
845  *r = t;
846  l++;
847  r--;
848  }
849  }
850  QuickSortSigIntId(sids, r - sids + 1);
851  QuickSortSigIntId(l, sids + n - l);
852 }
853 
854 #define SMS_USE_FLOW_SGH 0x01
855 #define SMS_USED_PM 0x02
856 #define SMS_USED_STREAM_PM 0x04
857 
858 /**
859  * \internal
860  * \brief Run mpm on packet, stream and other buffers based on
861  * alproto, sgh state.
862  *
863  * \param de_ctx Pointer to the detection engine context.
864  * \param det_ctx Pointer to the detection engine thread context.
865  * \param smsg The stream segment to inspect for stream mpm.
866  * \param p Packet.
867  * \param flags Flags.
868  * \param alproto Flow alproto.
869  * \param has_state Bool indicating we have (al)state
870  * \param sms_runflags Used to store state by detection engine.
871  */
872 static inline void DetectMpmPrefilter(DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx,
873  DetectEngineThreadCtx *det_ctx, StreamMsg *smsg, Packet *p,
874  const uint8_t flags, const AppProto alproto,
875  const int has_state, uint8_t *sms_runflags)
876 {
877  /* have a look at the reassembled stream (if any) */
878  if (p->flowflags & FLOW_PKT_ESTABLISHED) {
879  SCLogDebug("p->flowflags & FLOW_PKT_ESTABLISHED");
880 
881  /* all http based mpms */
882  if (has_state && alproto == ALPROTO_HTTP) {
883  FLOWLOCK_WRLOCK(p->flow);
884  void *alstate = FlowGetAppState(p->flow);
885  if (alstate == NULL) {
886  SCLogDebug("no alstate");
887  FLOWLOCK_UNLOCK(p->flow);
888  return;
889  }
890 
891  HtpState *htp_state = (HtpState *)alstate;
892  if (htp_state->connp == NULL) {
893  SCLogDebug("no HTTP connp");
894  FLOWLOCK_UNLOCK(p->flow);
895  return;
896  }
897 
898  int tx_progress = 0;
899  uint64_t idx = AppLayerParserGetTransactionInspectId(p->flow->alparser, flags);
900  uint64_t total_txs = AppLayerParserGetTxCnt(IPPROTO_TCP, ALPROTO_HTTP, alstate);
901  for (; idx < total_txs; idx++) {
902  htp_tx_t *tx = AppLayerParserGetTx(IPPROTO_TCP, ALPROTO_HTTP, htp_state, idx);
903  if (tx == NULL)
904  continue;
905 
906  if (p->flowflags & FLOW_PKT_TOSERVER) {
907  tx_progress = AppLayerParserGetStateProgress(IPPROTO_TCP, ALPROTO_HTTP, tx, flags);
908 
909  if (tx_progress > HTP_REQUEST_LINE) {
910  if (det_ctx->sgh->flags & SIG_GROUP_HEAD_MPM_URI) {
911  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_URI);
912  DetectUricontentInspectMpm(det_ctx, p->flow, alstate, flags, tx, idx);
913  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_URI);
914  }
915  if (det_ctx->sgh->flags & SIG_GROUP_HEAD_MPM_HRUD) {
916  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_HRUD);
917  DetectEngineRunHttpRawUriMpm(det_ctx, p->flow, alstate, flags, tx, idx);
918  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_HRUD);
919  }
920  if (det_ctx->sgh->flags & SIG_GROUP_HEAD_MPM_HMD) {
921  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_HMD);
922  DetectEngineRunHttpMethodMpm(det_ctx, p->flow, alstate, flags, tx, idx);
923  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_HMD);
924  }
925  }
926 
927  if (tx_progress >= HTP_REQUEST_HEADERS) {
928  if (det_ctx->sgh->flags & SIG_GROUP_HEAD_MPM_HHHD) {
929  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_HHHD);
930  DetectEngineRunHttpHHMpm(det_ctx, p->flow, alstate, flags, tx, idx);
931  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_HHHD);
932  }
933  if (det_ctx->sgh->flags & SIG_GROUP_HEAD_MPM_HRHHD) {
934  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_HRHHD);
935  DetectEngineRunHttpHRHMpm(det_ctx, p->flow, alstate, flags, tx, idx);
936  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_HRHHD);
937  }
938  if (det_ctx->sgh->flags & SIG_GROUP_HEAD_MPM_HCD) {
939  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_HCD);
940  DetectEngineRunHttpCookieMpm(det_ctx, p->flow, alstate, flags, tx, idx);
941  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_HCD);
942  }
943  if (det_ctx->sgh->flags & SIG_GROUP_HEAD_MPM_HUAD) {
944  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_HUAD);
945  DetectEngineRunHttpUAMpm(det_ctx, p->flow, alstate, flags, tx, idx);
946  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_HUAD);
947  }
948  if (det_ctx->sgh->flags & SIG_GROUP_HEAD_MPM_HHD) {
949  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_HHD);
950  DetectEngineRunHttpHeaderMpm(det_ctx, p->flow, alstate, flags, tx, idx);
951  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_HHD);
952  }
953  if (det_ctx->sgh->flags & SIG_GROUP_HEAD_MPM_HRHD) {
954  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_HRHD);
955  DetectEngineRunHttpRawHeaderMpm(det_ctx, p->flow, alstate, flags, tx, idx);
956  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_HRHD);
957  }
958  }
959 
960  if (tx_progress >= HTP_REQUEST_BODY) {
961  if (det_ctx->sgh->flags & SIG_GROUP_HEAD_MPM_HCBD) {
962  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_HCBD);
963  DetectEngineRunHttpClientBodyMpm(de_ctx, det_ctx, p->flow, alstate, flags, tx, idx);
964  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_HCBD);
965  }
966  }
967  } else { /* implied FLOW_PKT_TOCLIENT */
968  tx_progress = AppLayerParserGetStateProgress(IPPROTO_TCP, ALPROTO_HTTP, tx, flags);
969 
970  if (tx_progress > HTP_RESPONSE_LINE) {
971  if (det_ctx->sgh->flags & SIG_GROUP_HEAD_MPM_HSMD) {
972  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_HSMD);
973  DetectEngineRunHttpStatMsgMpm(det_ctx, p->flow, alstate, flags, tx, idx);
974  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_HSMD);
975  }
976  if (det_ctx->sgh->flags & SIG_GROUP_HEAD_MPM_HSCD) {
977  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_HSCD);
978  DetectEngineRunHttpStatCodeMpm(det_ctx, p->flow, alstate, flags, tx, idx);
979  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_HSCD);
980  }
981  }
982 
983  if (tx_progress >= HTP_RESPONSE_HEADERS) {
984  if (det_ctx->sgh->flags & SIG_GROUP_HEAD_MPM_HHD) {
985  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_HHD);
986  DetectEngineRunHttpHeaderMpm(det_ctx, p->flow, alstate, flags, tx, idx);
987  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_HHD);
988  }
989  if (det_ctx->sgh->flags & SIG_GROUP_HEAD_MPM_HRHD) {
990  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_HRHD);
991  DetectEngineRunHttpRawHeaderMpm(det_ctx, p->flow, alstate, flags, tx, idx);
992  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_HRHD);
993  }
994  if (det_ctx->sgh->flags & SIG_GROUP_HEAD_MPM_HCD) {
995  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_HCD);
996  DetectEngineRunHttpCookieMpm(det_ctx, p->flow, alstate, flags, tx, idx);
997  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_HCD);
998  }
999  }
1000 
1001  if (tx_progress >= HTP_RESPONSE_BODY) {
1002  if (det_ctx->sgh->flags & SIG_GROUP_HEAD_MPM_HSBD) {
1003  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_HSBD);
1004  DetectEngineRunHttpServerBodyMpm(de_ctx, det_ctx, p->flow, alstate, flags, tx, idx);
1005  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_HSBD);
1006  }
1007  }
1008  }
1009  } /* for */
1010 
1011  FLOWLOCK_UNLOCK(p->flow);
1012  }
1013  /* all dns based mpms */
1014  else if (alproto == ALPROTO_DNS && has_state) {
1015  if (p->flowflags & FLOW_PKT_TOSERVER) {
1016  if (det_ctx->sgh->flags & SIG_GROUP_HEAD_MPM_DNSQUERY) {
1017  FLOWLOCK_RDLOCK(p->flow);
1018  void *alstate = FlowGetAppState(p->flow);
1019  if (alstate == NULL) {
1020  SCLogDebug("no alstate");
1021  FLOWLOCK_UNLOCK(p->flow);
1022  return;
1023  }
1024 
1025  uint64_t idx = AppLayerParserGetTransactionInspectId(p->flow->alparser, flags);
1026  uint64_t total_txs = AppLayerParserGetTxCnt(p->flow->proto, alproto, alstate);
1027  for (; idx < total_txs; idx++) {
1028  void *tx = AppLayerParserGetTx(p->flow->proto, alproto, alstate, idx);
1029  if (tx == NULL)
1030  continue;
1031 
1032  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_DNSQUERY);
1033  DetectDnsQueryInspectMpm(det_ctx, p->flow, alstate, flags, tx, idx);
1034  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_DNSQUERY);
1035  }
1036  FLOWLOCK_UNLOCK(p->flow);
1037  }
1038  }
1039  } else if (alproto == ALPROTO_SMTP && has_state) {
1040  if (p->flowflags & FLOW_PKT_TOSERVER) {
1041  if (det_ctx->sgh->flags & SIG_GROUP_HEAD_MPM_FD_SMTP) {
1042  FLOWLOCK_RDLOCK(p->flow);
1043  void *alstate = FlowGetAppState(p->flow);
1044  if (alstate == NULL) {
1045  SCLogDebug("no alstate");
1046  FLOWLOCK_UNLOCK(p->flow);
1047  return;
1048  }
1049 
1050  SMTPState *smtp_state = (SMTPState *)alstate;
1051  uint64_t idx = AppLayerParserGetTransactionInspectId(p->flow->alparser, flags);
1052  uint64_t total_txs = AppLayerParserGetTxCnt(p->flow->proto, alproto, alstate);
1053  for (; idx < total_txs; idx++) {
1054  void *tx = AppLayerParserGetTx(p->flow->proto, alproto, alstate, idx);
1055  if (tx == NULL)
1056  continue;
1057 
1058  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_FD_SMTP);
1059  DetectEngineRunSMTPMpm(de_ctx, det_ctx, p->flow, smtp_state, flags, tx, idx);
1060  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_FD_SMTP);
1061  }
1062  FLOWLOCK_UNLOCK(p->flow);
1063  }
1064  }
1065  }
1066 
1067  if (smsg != NULL && (det_ctx->sgh->flags & SIG_GROUP_HEAD_MPM_STREAM)) {
1068  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_STREAM);
1069  StreamPatternSearch(det_ctx, p, smsg, flags);
1070  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_STREAM);
1071 
1072  *sms_runflags |= SMS_USED_STREAM_PM;
1073  } else {
1074  SCLogDebug("smsg NULL or no stream mpm for this sgh");
1075  }
1076  } else {
1077  SCLogDebug("NOT p->flowflags & FLOW_PKT_ESTABLISHED");
1078  }
1079 
1080  if (p->payload_len > 0 && (!(p->flags & PKT_NOPAYLOAD_INSPECTION))) {
1081  if (!(p->flags & PKT_STREAM_ADD) && (det_ctx->sgh->flags & SIG_GROUP_HEAD_MPM_STREAM)) {
1082  *sms_runflags |= SMS_USED_PM;
1083  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_PKT_STREAM);
1084  PacketPatternSearchWithStreamCtx(det_ctx, p);
1085  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_PKT_STREAM);
1086  }
1087  if (det_ctx->sgh->flags & SIG_GROUP_HEAD_MPM_PACKET) {
1088  /* run the multi packet matcher against the payload of the packet */
1089  SCLogDebug("search: (%p, minlen %" PRIu32 ", sgh->sig_cnt %" PRIu32 ")",
1090  det_ctx->sgh, det_ctx->sgh->mpm_content_minlen, det_ctx->sgh->sig_cnt);
1091 
1092  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_PACKET);
1093  PacketPatternSearch(det_ctx, p);
1094  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_PACKET);
1095 
1096  *sms_runflags |= SMS_USED_PM;
1097  }
1098  }
1099 
1100  /* UDP DNS inspection is independent of est or not */
1101  if (alproto == ALPROTO_DNS && has_state) {
1102  if (p->flowflags & FLOW_PKT_TOSERVER) {
1103  SCLogDebug("mpm inspection");
1104  if (det_ctx->sgh->flags & SIG_GROUP_HEAD_MPM_DNSQUERY) {
1105  FLOWLOCK_RDLOCK(p->flow);
1106  void *alstate = FlowGetAppState(p->flow);
1107  if (alstate == NULL) {
1108  SCLogDebug("no alstate");
1109  FLOWLOCK_UNLOCK(p->flow);
1110  return;
1111  }
1112 
1113  uint64_t idx = AppLayerParserGetTransactionInspectId(p->flow->alparser, flags);
1114  uint64_t total_txs = AppLayerParserGetTxCnt(p->flow->proto, alproto, alstate);
1115  for (; idx < total_txs; idx++) {
1116  void *tx = AppLayerParserGetTx(p->flow->proto, alproto, alstate, idx);
1117  if (tx == NULL)
1118  continue;
1119  SCLogDebug("tx %p",tx);
1120  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_DNSQUERY);
1121  DetectDnsQueryInspectMpm(det_ctx, p->flow, alstate, flags, tx, idx);
1122  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM_DNSQUERY);
1123  }
1124  FLOWLOCK_UNLOCK(p->flow);
1125  }
1126  }
1127  }
1128 
1129  /* Sort the rule list to lets look at pmq.
1130  * NOTE due to merging of 'stream' pmqs we *MAY* have duplicate entries */
1131  if (det_ctx->pmq.rule_id_array_cnt > 1) {
1132  QuickSortSigIntId(det_ctx->pmq.rule_id_array, det_ctx->pmq.rule_id_array_cnt);
1133  }
1134 }
1135 
1136 #ifdef DEBUG
1137 static void DebugInspectIds(Packet *p, Flow *f, StreamMsg *smsg)
1138 {
1139  SCLogDebug("pcap_cnt %02"PRIu64", %s, %12s, smsg %s",
1140  p->pcap_cnt, p->flowflags & FLOW_PKT_TOSERVER ? "toserver" : "toclient",
1141  p->flags & PKT_STREAM_EST ? "established" : "stateless",
1142  smsg ? "yes" : "no");
1143  AppLayerParserStatePrintDetails(f->alparser);
1144 }
1145 #endif
1146 
1147 static void AlertDebugLogModeSyncFlowbitsNamesToPacketStruct(Packet *p, DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx)
1148 {
1149 #define MALLOC_JUMP 5
1150 
1151  int i = 0;
1152 
1153  GenericVar *gv = p->flow->flowvar;
1154 
1155  while (gv != NULL) {
1156  i++;
1157  gv = gv->next;
1158  }
1159  if (i == 0)
1160  return;
1161 
1162  p->debuglog_flowbits_names_len = i;
1163 
1164  p->debuglog_flowbits_names = SCMalloc(sizeof(char *) *
1165  p->debuglog_flowbits_names_len);
1166  if (p->debuglog_flowbits_names == NULL) {
1167  return;
1168  }
1169  memset(p->debuglog_flowbits_names, 0,
1170  sizeof(char *) * p->debuglog_flowbits_names_len);
1171 
1172  i = 0;
1173  gv = p->flow->flowvar;
1174  while (gv != NULL) {
1175  if (gv->type != DETECT_FLOWBITS) {
1176  gv = gv->next;
1177  continue;
1178  }
1179 
1180  FlowBit *fb = (FlowBit *) gv;
1181  char *name = VariableIdxGetName(de_ctx, fb->idx, VAR_TYPE_FLOW_BIT);
1182  if (name != NULL) {
1183  p->debuglog_flowbits_names[i] = SCStrdup(name);
1184  if (p->debuglog_flowbits_names[i] == NULL) {
1185  return;
1186  }
1187  i++;
1188  }
1189 
1190  if (i == p->debuglog_flowbits_names_len) {
1191  p->debuglog_flowbits_names_len += MALLOC_JUMP;
1192  const char **names = SCRealloc(p->debuglog_flowbits_names,
1193  sizeof(char *) *
1194  p->debuglog_flowbits_names_len);
1195  if (names == NULL) {
1196  SCFree(p->debuglog_flowbits_names);
1197  p->debuglog_flowbits_names = NULL;
1198  p->debuglog_flowbits_names_len = 0;
1199  return;
1200  }
1201  p->debuglog_flowbits_names = names;
1202  memset(p->debuglog_flowbits_names +
1203  p->debuglog_flowbits_names_len - MALLOC_JUMP,
1204  0, sizeof(char *) * MALLOC_JUMP);
1205  }
1206 
1207  gv = gv->next;
1208  }
1209 
1210  return;
1211 }
1212 
1213 static inline void DetectPrefilterBuildNonMpmList(DetectEngineThreadCtx *det_ctx, SignatureMask mask)
1214 {
1215  uint32_t x = 0;
1216  for (x = 0; x < det_ctx->sgh->non_mpm_store_cnt; x++) {
1217  /* only if the mask matches this rule can possibly match,
1218  * so build the non_mpm array only for match candidates */
1219  SignatureMask rule_mask = det_ctx->sgh->non_mpm_store_array[x].mask;
1220  if ((rule_mask & mask) == rule_mask) {
1221  det_ctx->non_mpm_id_array[det_ctx->non_mpm_id_cnt++] = det_ctx->sgh->non_mpm_store_array[x].id;
1222  }
1223  }
1224 }
1225 
1226 /**
1227  * \brief Signature match function
1228  *
1229  * \retval 1 one or more signatures matched
1230  * \retval 0 no matches were found
1231  */
1232 int SigMatchSignatures(ThreadVars *th_v, DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx, DetectEngineThreadCtx *det_ctx, Packet *p)
1233 {
1234  uint8_t sms_runflags = 0; /* function flags */
1235  uint8_t alert_flags = 0;
1236  AppProto alproto = ALPROTO_UNKNOWN;
1237 #ifdef PROFILING
1238  int smatch = 0; /* signature match: 1, no match: 0 */
1239 #endif
1240  uint8_t flow_flags = 0; /* flow/state flags */
1241  StreamMsg *smsg = NULL;
1242  Signature *s = NULL;
1243  Signature *next_s = NULL;
1244  uint8_t alversion = 0;
1245  int state_alert = 0;
1246  int alerts = 0;
1247  int app_decoder_events = 0;
1248  int has_state = 0; /* do we have an alstate to work with? */
1249 
1250  SCEnter();
1251 
1252  SCLogDebug("pcap_cnt %"PRIu64, p->pcap_cnt);
1253 
1254  p->alerts.cnt = 0;
1255  det_ctx->filestore_cnt = 0;
1256 
1257  /* No need to perform any detection on this packet, if the the given flag is set.*/
1258  if (p->flags & PKT_NOPACKET_INSPECTION) {
1259  SCReturnInt(0);
1260  }
1261 
1262  /* Load the Packet's flow early, even though it might not be needed.
1263  * Mark as a constant pointer, although the flow can change.
1264  */
1265  Flow * const pflow = p->flow;
1266 
1267  /* grab the protocol state we will detect on */
1268  if (p->flags & PKT_HAS_FLOW) {
1269  if (p->flowflags & FLOW_PKT_TOSERVER) {
1270  flow_flags = STREAM_TOSERVER;
1271  SCLogDebug("flag STREAM_TOSERVER set");
1272  } else if (p->flowflags & FLOW_PKT_TOCLIENT) {
1273  flow_flags = STREAM_TOCLIENT;
1274  SCLogDebug("flag STREAM_TOCLIENT set");
1275  }
1276  SCLogDebug("p->flowflags 0x%02x", p->flowflags);
1277 
1278  if (p->flags & PKT_STREAM_EOF) {
1279  flow_flags |= STREAM_EOF;
1280  SCLogDebug("STREAM_EOF set");
1281  }
1282 
1283  FLOWLOCK_WRLOCK(pflow);
1284  {
1285  /* store tenant_id in the flow so that we can use it
1286  * for creating pseudo packets */
1287  if (p->tenant_id > 0 && pflow->tenant_id == 0) {
1288  pflow->tenant_id = p->tenant_id;
1289  }
1290 
1291  /* live ruleswap check for flow updates */
1292  if (pflow->de_ctx_id == 0) {
1293  /* first time this flow is inspected, set id */
1294  pflow->de_ctx_id = de_ctx->id;
1295  } else if (pflow->de_ctx_id != de_ctx->id) {
1296  /* first time we inspect flow with this de_ctx, reset */
1297  pflow->flags &= ~FLOW_SGH_TOSERVER;
1298  pflow->flags &= ~FLOW_SGH_TOCLIENT;
1299  pflow->sgh_toserver = NULL;
1300  pflow->sgh_toclient = NULL;
1301 
1302  pflow->de_ctx_id = de_ctx->id;
1303  GenericVarFree(pflow->flowvar);
1304  pflow->flowvar = NULL;
1305 
1306  DetectEngineStateReset(pflow->de_state,
1307  (STREAM_TOSERVER|STREAM_TOCLIENT));
1308  DetectEngineStateResetTxs(pflow);
1309  }
1310 
1311  /* set the iponly stuff */
1312  if (pflow->flags & FLOW_TOCLIENT_IPONLY_SET)
1313  p->flowflags |= FLOW_PKT_TOCLIENT_IPONLY_SET;
1314  if (pflow->flags & FLOW_TOSERVER_IPONLY_SET)
1315  p->flowflags |= FLOW_PKT_TOSERVER_IPONLY_SET;
1316 
1317  /* Get the stored sgh from the flow (if any). Make sure we're not using
1318  * the sgh for icmp error packets part of the same stream. */
1319  if (IP_GET_IPPROTO(p) == pflow->proto) { /* filter out icmp */
1320  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_GETSGH);
1321  if ((p->flowflags & FLOW_PKT_TOSERVER) && (pflow->flags & FLOW_SGH_TOSERVER)) {
1322  det_ctx->sgh = pflow->sgh_toserver;
1323  sms_runflags |= SMS_USE_FLOW_SGH;
1324  } else if ((p->flowflags & FLOW_PKT_TOCLIENT) && (pflow->flags & FLOW_SGH_TOCLIENT)) {
1325  det_ctx->sgh = pflow->sgh_toclient;
1326  sms_runflags |= SMS_USE_FLOW_SGH;
1327  }
1328  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_GETSGH);
1329 
1330  smsg = SigMatchSignaturesGetSmsg(pflow, p, flow_flags);
1331 #if 0
1332  StreamMsg *tmpsmsg = smsg;
1333  while (tmpsmsg) {
1334  printf("detect ---start---:\n");
1335  PrintRawDataFp(stdout,tmpsmsg->data.data,tmpsmsg->data.data_len);
1336  printf("detect ---end---:\n");
1337  tmpsmsg = tmpsmsg->next;
1338  }
1339 #endif
1340  }
1341 
1342  /* Retrieve the app layer state and protocol and the tcp reassembled
1343  * stream chunks. */
1344  if ((p->proto == IPPROTO_TCP && (p->flags & PKT_STREAM_EST)) ||
1345  (p->proto == IPPROTO_UDP) ||
1346  (p->proto == IPPROTO_SCTP && (p->flowflags & FLOW_PKT_ESTABLISHED)))
1347  {
1348  /* update flow flags with knowledge on disruptions */
1349  flow_flags = FlowGetDisruptionFlags(pflow, flow_flags);
1350  has_state = (FlowGetAppState(pflow) != NULL);
1351  alproto = FlowGetAppProtocol(pflow);
1352  alversion = AppLayerParserGetStateVersion(pflow->alparser);
1353  SCLogDebug("alstate %s, alproto %u", has_state ? "true" : "false", alproto);
1354  } else {
1355  SCLogDebug("packet doesn't have established flag set (proto %d)", p->proto);
1356  }
1357 
1358  app_decoder_events = AppLayerParserHasDecoderEvents(pflow->proto,
1359  pflow->alproto,
1360  pflow->alstate,
1361  pflow->alparser,
1362  flow_flags);
1363  }
1364  FLOWLOCK_UNLOCK(pflow);
1365 
1366  if (((p->flowflags & FLOW_PKT_TOSERVER) && !(p->flowflags & FLOW_PKT_TOSERVER_IPONLY_SET)) ||
1367  ((p->flowflags & FLOW_PKT_TOCLIENT) && !(p->flowflags & FLOW_PKT_TOCLIENT_IPONLY_SET)))
1368  {
1369  SCLogDebug("testing against \"ip-only\" signatures");
1370 
1371  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_IPONLY);
1372  IPOnlyMatchPacket(th_v, de_ctx, det_ctx, &de_ctx->io_ctx, &det_ctx->io_ctx, p);
1373  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_IPONLY);
1374 
1375  /* save in the flow that we scanned this direction... locking is
1376  * done in the FlowSetIPOnlyFlag function. */
1377  FlowSetIPOnlyFlag(pflow, p->flowflags & FLOW_PKT_TOSERVER ? 1 : 0);
1378 
1379  } else if (((p->flowflags & FLOW_PKT_TOSERVER) &&
1380  (pflow->flags & FLOW_TOSERVER_IPONLY_SET)) ||
1381  ((p->flowflags & FLOW_PKT_TOCLIENT) &&
1382  (pflow->flags & FLOW_TOCLIENT_IPONLY_SET)))
1383  {
1384  /* If we have a drop from IP only module,
1385  * we will drop the rest of the flow packets
1386  * This will apply only to inline/IPS */
1387  if (pflow->flags & FLOW_ACTION_DROP)
1388  {
1389  alert_flags = PACKET_ALERT_FLAG_DROP_FLOW;
1390  PACKET_DROP(p);
1391  }
1392  }
1393 
1394  if (!(sms_runflags & SMS_USE_FLOW_SGH)) {
1395  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_GETSGH);
1396  det_ctx->sgh = SigMatchSignaturesGetSgh(de_ctx, det_ctx, p);
1397  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_GETSGH);
1398  }
1399 
1400 #ifdef DEBUG
1401  if (pflow) {
1402  SCMutexLock(&pflow->m);
1403  DebugInspectIds(p, pflow, smsg);
1404  SCMutexUnlock(&pflow->m);
1405  }
1406 #endif
1407  } else { /* p->flags & PKT_HAS_FLOW */
1408  /* no flow */
1409 
1410  /* Even without flow we should match the packet src/dst */
1411  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_IPONLY);
1412  IPOnlyMatchPacket(th_v, de_ctx, det_ctx, &de_ctx->io_ctx,
1413  &det_ctx->io_ctx, p);
1414  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_IPONLY);
1415 
1416  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_GETSGH);
1417  det_ctx->sgh = SigMatchSignaturesGetSgh(de_ctx, det_ctx, p);
1418  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_GETSGH);
1419  }
1420 
1421  /* if we didn't get a sig group head, we
1422  * have nothing to do.... */
1423  if (det_ctx->sgh == NULL) {
1424  SCLogDebug("no sgh for this packet, nothing to match against");
1425  goto end;
1426  }
1427 
1428  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_STATEFUL);
1429  /* stateful app layer detection */
1430  if ((p->flags & PKT_HAS_FLOW) && has_state) {
1431  memset(det_ctx->de_state_sig_array, 0x00, det_ctx->de_state_sig_array_len);
1432  int has_inspectable_state = DeStateFlowHasInspectableState(pflow, alproto, alversion, flow_flags);
1433  if (has_inspectable_state == 1) {
1434  /* initialize to 0(DE_STATE_MATCH_HAS_NEW_STATE) */
1435  DeStateDetectContinueDetection(th_v, de_ctx, det_ctx, p, pflow,
1436  flow_flags, alproto, alversion);
1437  } else if (has_inspectable_state == 2) {
1438  /* no inspectable state, so pretend we don't have a state at all */
1439  has_state = 0;
1440  }
1441  }
1442  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_STATEFUL);
1443 
1444  /* create our prefilter mask */
1445  SignatureMask mask = 0;
1446  PacketCreateMask(p, &mask, alproto, has_state, smsg, app_decoder_events);
1447 
1448  /* build and prefilter non_mpm list against the mask of the packet */
1449  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_NONMPMLIST);
1450  det_ctx->non_mpm_id_cnt = 0;
1451  if (likely(det_ctx->sgh->non_mpm_store_cnt > 0)) {
1452  DetectPrefilterBuildNonMpmList(det_ctx, mask);
1453  }
1454  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_NONMPMLIST);
1455 
1456  /* run the mpm for each type */
1457  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM);
1458  DetectMpmPrefilter(de_ctx, det_ctx, smsg, p, flow_flags, alproto, has_state, &sms_runflags);
1459  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_MPM);
1460 #ifdef PROFILING
1461  if (th_v) {
1462  StatsAddUI64(th_v, det_ctx->counter_mpm_list,
1463  (uint64_t)det_ctx->pmq.rule_id_array_cnt);
1464  StatsAddUI64(th_v, det_ctx->counter_nonmpm_list,
1465  (uint64_t)det_ctx->sgh->non_mpm_store_cnt);
1466  /* non mpm sigs after mask prefilter */
1467  StatsAddUI64(th_v, det_ctx->counter_fnonmpm_list,
1468  (uint64_t)det_ctx->non_mpm_id_cnt);
1469  }
1470 #endif
1471 
1472  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_PREFILTER);
1473  DetectPrefilterMergeSort(de_ctx, det_ctx);
1474  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_PREFILTER);
1475 
1476  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_RULES);
1477  /* inspect the sigs against the packet */
1478  /* Prefetch the next signature. */
1479  SigIntId match_cnt = det_ctx->match_array_cnt;
1480 #ifdef PROFILING
1481  if (th_v) {
1482  StatsAddUI64(th_v, det_ctx->counter_match_list,
1483  (uint64_t)match_cnt);
1484  }
1485 #endif
1486  Signature **match_array = det_ctx->match_array;
1487 
1488  uint32_t sflags, next_sflags = 0;
1489  if (match_cnt) {
1490  next_s = *match_array++;
1491  next_sflags = next_s->flags;
1492  }
1493 
1494  while (match_cnt--) {
1495  RULE_PROFILING_START(p);
1496  state_alert = 0;
1497 #ifdef PROFILING
1498  smatch = 0;
1499 #endif
1500 
1501  s = next_s;
1502  sflags = next_sflags;
1503  if (match_cnt) {
1504  next_s = *match_array++;
1505  next_sflags = next_s->flags;
1506  }
1507  uint8_t s_proto_flags = s->proto.flags;
1508 
1509  SCLogDebug("inspecting signature id %"PRIu32"", s->id);
1510 
1511  /* if the sig has alproto and the session as well they should match */
1512  if (likely(sflags & SIG_FLAG_APPLAYER)) {
1513  if (s->alproto != ALPROTO_UNKNOWN && s->alproto != alproto) {
1514  if (s->alproto == ALPROTO_DCERPC) {
1515  if (alproto != ALPROTO_SMB && alproto != ALPROTO_SMB2) {
1516  SCLogDebug("DCERPC sig, alproto not SMB or SMB2");
1517  goto next;
1518  }
1519  } else {
1520  SCLogDebug("alproto mismatch");
1521  goto next;
1522  }
1523  }
1524  }
1525 
1526  if (unlikely(sflags & SIG_FLAG_DSIZE)) {
1527  if (likely(p->payload_len < s->dsize_low || p->payload_len > s->dsize_high)) {
1528  SCLogDebug("kicked out as p->payload_len %u, dsize low %u, hi %u",
1529  p->payload_len, s->dsize_low, s->dsize_high);
1530  goto next;
1531  }
1532  }
1533 
1534  /* check for a pattern match of the one pattern in this sig. */
1535  if (likely(sflags & (SIG_FLAG_MPM_PACKET|SIG_FLAG_MPM_STREAM|SIG_FLAG_MPM_APPLAYER))) {
1536  /* filter out sigs that want pattern matches, but
1537  * have no matches */
1538  if (!(det_ctx->pmq.pattern_id_bitarray[(s->mpm_pattern_id_div_8)] & s->mpm_pattern_id_mod_8)) {
1539  if (sflags & SIG_FLAG_MPM_PACKET) {
1540  if (!(sflags & SIG_FLAG_MPM_PACKET_NEG)) {
1541  goto next;
1542  }
1543  } else if (sflags & SIG_FLAG_MPM_STREAM) {
1544  /* filter out sigs that want pattern matches, but
1545  * have no matches */
1546  if (!(sflags & SIG_FLAG_MPM_STREAM_NEG)) {
1547  goto next;
1548  }
1549  } else if (sflags & SIG_FLAG_MPM_APPLAYER) {
1550  if (!(sflags & SIG_FLAG_MPM_APPLAYER_NEG)) {
1551  goto next;
1552  }
1553  }
1554  }
1555  }
1556  if (sflags & SIG_FLAG_STATE_MATCH) {
1557  if (det_ctx->de_state_sig_array[s->num] & DE_STATE_MATCH_NO_NEW_STATE)
1558  goto next;
1559  }
1560 
1561  /* check if this signature has a requirement for flowvars of some type
1562  * and if so, if we actually have any in the flow. If not, the sig
1563  * can't match and we skip it. */
1564  if ((p->flags & PKT_HAS_FLOW) && (sflags & SIG_FLAG_REQUIRE_FLOWVAR)) {
1565  FLOWLOCK_RDLOCK(pflow);
1566  int m = pflow->flowvar ? 1 : 0;
1567  FLOWLOCK_UNLOCK(pflow);
1568 
1569  /* no flowvars? skip this sig */
1570  if (m == 0) {
1571  SCLogDebug("skipping sig as the flow has no flowvars and sig "
1572  "has SIG_FLAG_REQUIRE_FLOWVAR flag set.");
1573  goto next;
1574  }
1575  }
1576 
1577  if ((s_proto_flags & DETECT_PROTO_IPV4) && !PKT_IS_IPV4(p)) {
1578  SCLogDebug("ip version didn't match");
1579  goto next;
1580  }
1581  if ((s_proto_flags & DETECT_PROTO_IPV6) && !PKT_IS_IPV6(p)) {
1582  SCLogDebug("ip version didn't match");
1583  goto next;
1584  }
1585 
1586  if (DetectProtoContainsProto(&s->proto, IP_GET_IPPROTO(p)) == 0) {
1587  SCLogDebug("proto didn't match");
1588  goto next;
1589  }
1590 
1591  /* check the source & dst port in the sig */
1592  if (p->proto == IPPROTO_TCP || p->proto == IPPROTO_UDP || p->proto == IPPROTO_SCTP) {
1593  if (!(sflags & SIG_FLAG_DP_ANY)) {
1594  if (p->flags & PKT_IS_FRAGMENT)
1595  goto next;
1596  DetectPort *dport = DetectPortLookupGroup(s->dp,p->dp);
1597  if (dport == NULL) {
1598  SCLogDebug("dport didn't match.");
1599  goto next;
1600  }
1601  }
1602  if (!(sflags & SIG_FLAG_SP_ANY)) {
1603  if (p->flags & PKT_IS_FRAGMENT)
1604  goto next;
1605  DetectPort *sport = DetectPortLookupGroup(s->sp,p->sp);
1606  if (sport == NULL) {
1607  SCLogDebug("sport didn't match.");
1608  goto next;
1609  }
1610  }
1611  } else if ((sflags & (SIG_FLAG_DP_ANY|SIG_FLAG_SP_ANY)) != (SIG_FLAG_DP_ANY|SIG_FLAG_SP_ANY)) {
1612  SCLogDebug("port-less protocol and sig needs ports");
1613  goto next;
1614  }
1615 
1616  /* check the destination address */
1617  if (!(sflags & SIG_FLAG_DST_ANY)) {
1618  if (PKT_IS_IPV4(p)) {
1619  if (DetectAddressMatchIPv4(s->addr_dst_match4, s->addr_dst_match4_cnt, &p->dst) == 0)
1620  goto next;
1621  } else if (PKT_IS_IPV6(p)) {
1622  if (DetectAddressMatchIPv6(s->addr_dst_match6, s->addr_dst_match6_cnt, &p->dst) == 0)
1623  goto next;
1624  }
1625  }
1626  /* check the source address */
1627  if (!(sflags & SIG_FLAG_SRC_ANY)) {
1628  if (PKT_IS_IPV4(p)) {
1629  if (DetectAddressMatchIPv4(s->addr_src_match4, s->addr_src_match4_cnt, &p->src) == 0)
1630  goto next;
1631  } else if (PKT_IS_IPV6(p)) {
1632  if (DetectAddressMatchIPv6(s->addr_src_match6, s->addr_src_match6_cnt, &p->src) == 0)
1633  goto next;
1634  }
1635  }
1636 
1637  /* Check the payload keywords. If we are a MPM sig and we've made
1638  * to here, we've had at least one of the patterns match */
1639  if (s->sm_arrays[DETECT_SM_LIST_PMATCH] != NULL) {
1640  KEYWORD_PROFILING_SET_LIST(det_ctx, DETECT_SM_LIST_PMATCH);
1641  /* if we have stream msgs, inspect against those first,
1642  * but not for a "dsize" signature */
1643  if (sflags & SIG_FLAG_REQUIRE_STREAM) {
1644  char pmatch = 0;
1645  if (smsg != NULL) {
1646  uint8_t pmq_idx = 0;
1647  StreamMsg *smsg_inspect = smsg;
1648  for ( ; smsg_inspect != NULL; smsg_inspect = smsg_inspect->next, pmq_idx++) {
1649  /* filter out sigs that want pattern matches, but
1650  * have no matches */
1651  if ((sflags & SIG_FLAG_MPM_STREAM) && !(sflags & SIG_FLAG_MPM_STREAM_NEG) &&
1652  !(det_ctx->smsg_pmq[pmq_idx].pattern_id_bitarray[(s->mpm_pattern_id_div_8)] & s->mpm_pattern_id_mod_8)) {
1653  SCLogDebug("no match in this smsg");
1654  continue;
1655  }
1656 
1657  if (DetectEngineInspectStreamPayload(de_ctx, det_ctx, s, pflow, smsg_inspect->data, smsg_inspect->data_len) == 1) {
1658  SCLogDebug("match in smsg %p", smsg);
1659  pmatch = 1;
1660  det_ctx->flags |= DETECT_ENGINE_THREAD_CTX_STREAM_CONTENT_MATCH;
1661  /* Tell the engine that this reassembled stream can drop the
1662  * rest of the pkts with no further inspection */
1663  if (s->action & ACTION_DROP)
1664  alert_flags |= PACKET_ALERT_FLAG_DROP_FLOW;
1665 
1666  alert_flags |= PACKET_ALERT_FLAG_STREAM_MATCH;
1667  break;
1668  }
1669  }
1670 
1671  } /* if (smsg != NULL) */
1672 
1673  /* no match? then inspect packet payload */
1674  if (pmatch == 0) {
1675  SCLogDebug("no match in smsg, fall back to packet payload");
1676 
1677  if (!(sflags & SIG_FLAG_REQUIRE_PACKET)) {
1678  if (p->flags & PKT_STREAM_ADD)
1679  goto next;
1680  }
1681 
1682  if (sms_runflags & SMS_USED_PM) {
1683  if ((sflags & SIG_FLAG_MPM_PACKET) && !(sflags & SIG_FLAG_MPM_PACKET_NEG) &&
1684  !(det_ctx->pmq.pattern_id_bitarray[(s->mpm_pattern_id_div_8)] &
1685  s->mpm_pattern_id_mod_8)) {
1686  goto next;
1687  }
1688  if (DetectEngineInspectPacketPayload(de_ctx, det_ctx, s, pflow, p) != 1) {
1689  goto next;
1690  }
1691  } else {
1692  if (DetectEngineInspectPacketPayload(de_ctx, det_ctx, s, pflow, p) != 1) {
1693  goto next;
1694  }
1695  }
1696  }
1697  } else {
1698  if (sms_runflags & SMS_USED_PM) {
1699  if ((sflags & SIG_FLAG_MPM_PACKET) && !(sflags & SIG_FLAG_MPM_PACKET_NEG) &&
1700  !(det_ctx->pmq.pattern_id_bitarray[(s->mpm_pattern_id_div_8)] &
1701  s->mpm_pattern_id_mod_8)) {
1702  goto next;
1703  }
1704  if (DetectEngineInspectPacketPayload(de_ctx, det_ctx, s, pflow, p) != 1) {
1705  goto next;
1706  }
1707  } else {
1708  if (DetectEngineInspectPacketPayload(de_ctx, det_ctx, s, pflow, p) != 1)
1709  goto next;
1710  }
1711  }
1712  }
1713 
1714  /* run the packet match functions */
1715  if (s->sm_arrays[DETECT_SM_LIST_MATCH] != NULL) {
1716  KEYWORD_PROFILING_SET_LIST(det_ctx, DETECT_SM_LIST_MATCH);
1717  SigMatchData *smd = s->sm_arrays[DETECT_SM_LIST_MATCH];
1718 
1719  SCLogDebug("running match functions, sm %p", smd);
1720  if (smd != NULL) {
1721  while (1) {
1722  KEYWORD_PROFILING_START;
1723  if (sigmatch_table[smd->type].Match(th_v, det_ctx, p, s, smd->ctx) <= 0) {
1724  KEYWORD_PROFILING_END(det_ctx, smd->type, 0);
1725  goto next;
1726  }
1727  KEYWORD_PROFILING_END(det_ctx, smd->type, 1);
1728  if (smd->is_last)
1729  break;
1730  smd++;
1731  }
1732  }
1733  }
1734 
1735  SCLogDebug("s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_AMATCH] %p, "
1736  "s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_UMATCH] %p, "
1737  "s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_DMATCH] %p, "
1738  "s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HCDMATCH] %p",
1739  s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_AMATCH],
1740  s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_UMATCH],
1741  s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_DMATCH],
1742  s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HCDMATCH]);
1743 
1744  /* consider stateful sig matches */
1745  if (sflags & SIG_FLAG_STATE_MATCH) {
1746  if (has_state == 0) {
1747  SCLogDebug("state matches but no state, we can't match");
1748  goto next;
1749  }
1750 
1751  SCLogDebug("stateful app layer match inspection starting");
1752 
1753  /* if DeStateDetectStartDetection matches, it's a full
1754  * signature match. It will then call PacketAlertAppend
1755  * itself, so we can skip it below. This is done so it
1756  * can store the tx_id with the alert */
1757  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_STATEFUL);
1758  state_alert = DeStateDetectStartDetection(th_v, de_ctx, det_ctx, s,
1759  p, pflow, flow_flags, alproto, alversion);
1760  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_STATEFUL);
1761  if (state_alert == 0)
1762  goto next;
1763 
1764  /* match */
1765  if (s->action & ACTION_DROP)
1766  alert_flags |= PACKET_ALERT_FLAG_DROP_FLOW;
1767 
1768  alert_flags |= PACKET_ALERT_FLAG_STATE_MATCH;
1769  }
1770 
1771 #ifdef PROFILING
1772  smatch = 1;
1773 #endif
1774 
1775  SigMatchSignaturesRunPostMatch(th_v, de_ctx, det_ctx, p, s);
1776 
1777  if (!(sflags & SIG_FLAG_NOALERT)) {
1778  /* stateful sigs call PacketAlertAppend from DeStateDetectStartDetection */
1779  if (!state_alert)
1780  PacketAlertAppend(det_ctx, s, p, 0, alert_flags);
1781  } else {
1782  /* apply actions even if not alerting */
1783  DetectSignatureApplyActions(p, s);
1784  }
1785  alerts++;
1786 next:
1787  DetectFlowvarProcessList(det_ctx, pflow);
1788  DetectReplaceFree(det_ctx);
1789  RULE_PROFILING_END(det_ctx, s, smatch, p);
1790 
1791  det_ctx->flags = 0;
1792  continue;
1793  }
1794  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_RULES);
1795 
1796 end:
1797 #ifdef __SC_CUDA_SUPPORT__
1798  CudaReleasePacket(p);
1799 #endif
1800 
1801  /* see if we need to increment the inspect_id and reset the de_state */
1802  if (has_state && AppLayerParserProtocolSupportsTxs(p->proto, alproto)) {
1803  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_STATEFUL);
1804  DeStateUpdateInspectTransactionId(pflow, flow_flags);
1805  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_STATEFUL);
1806  }
1807 
1808  /* so now let's iterate the alerts and remove the ones after a pass rule
1809  * matched (if any). This is done inside PacketAlertFinalize() */
1810  /* PR: installed "tag" keywords are handled after the threshold inspection */
1811 
1812  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_ALERT);
1813  PacketAlertFinalize(de_ctx, det_ctx, p);
1814  if (p->alerts.cnt > 0) {
1815  StatsAddUI64(th_v, det_ctx->counter_alerts, (uint64_t)p->alerts.cnt);
1816  }
1817  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_ALERT);
1818 
1819  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_START(p, PROF_DETECT_CLEANUP);
1820  /* cleanup pkt specific part of the patternmatcher */
1821  PacketPatternCleanup(th_v, det_ctx);
1822 
1823  DetectEngineCleanHCBDBuffers(det_ctx);
1824  DetectEngineCleanHSBDBuffers(det_ctx);
1825  DetectEngineCleanHHDBuffers(det_ctx);
1826 
1827  /* store the found sgh (or NULL) in the flow to save us from looking it
1828  * up again for the next packet. Also return any stream chunk we processed
1829  * to the pool. */
1830  if (p->flags & PKT_HAS_FLOW) {
1831  if (sms_runflags & SMS_USED_STREAM_PM) {
1832  StreamPatternCleanup(th_v, det_ctx, smsg);
1833  }
1834 
1835  FLOWLOCK_WRLOCK(pflow);
1836  if (debuglog_enabled) {
1837  if (p->alerts.cnt > 0) {
1838  AlertDebugLogModeSyncFlowbitsNamesToPacketStruct(p, de_ctx);
1839  }
1840  }
1841 
1842  if (!(sms_runflags & SMS_USE_FLOW_SGH)) {
1843  if ((p->flowflags & FLOW_PKT_TOSERVER) && !(pflow->flags & FLOW_SGH_TOSERVER)) {
1844  /* first time we see this toserver sgh, store it */
1845  pflow->sgh_toserver = det_ctx->sgh;
1846  pflow->flags |= FLOW_SGH_TOSERVER;
1847 
1848  /* see if this sgh requires us to consider file storing */
1849  if (pflow->sgh_toserver == NULL || pflow->sgh_toserver->filestore_cnt == 0) {
1850  FileDisableStoring(pflow, STREAM_TOSERVER);
1851  }
1852 
1853  /* see if this sgh requires us to consider file magic */
1854  if (!FileForceMagic() && (pflow->sgh_toserver == NULL ||
1855  !(pflow->sgh_toserver->flags & SIG_GROUP_HEAD_HAVEFILEMAGIC)))
1856  {
1857  SCLogDebug("disabling magic for flow");
1858  FileDisableMagic(pflow, STREAM_TOSERVER);
1859  }
1860 
1861  /* see if this sgh requires us to consider file md5 */
1862  if (!FileForceMd5() && (pflow->sgh_toserver == NULL ||
1863  !(pflow->sgh_toserver->flags & SIG_GROUP_HEAD_HAVEFILEMD5)))
1864  {
1865  SCLogDebug("disabling md5 for flow");
1866  FileDisableMd5(pflow, STREAM_TOSERVER);
1867  }
1868 
1869  /* see if this sgh requires us to consider filesize */
1870  if (pflow->sgh_toserver == NULL ||
1871  !(pflow->sgh_toserver->flags & SIG_GROUP_HEAD_HAVEFILESIZE))
1872  {
1873  SCLogDebug("disabling filesize for flow");
1874  FileDisableFilesize(pflow, STREAM_TOSERVER);
1875  }
1876  } else if ((p->flowflags & FLOW_PKT_TOCLIENT) && !(pflow->flags & FLOW_SGH_TOCLIENT)) {
1877  pflow->sgh_toclient = det_ctx->sgh;
1878  pflow->flags |= FLOW_SGH_TOCLIENT;
1879 
1880  if (pflow->sgh_toclient == NULL || pflow->sgh_toclient->filestore_cnt == 0) {
1881  FileDisableStoring(pflow, STREAM_TOCLIENT);
1882  }
1883 
1884  /* check if this flow needs magic, if not disable it */
1885  if (!FileForceMagic() && (pflow->sgh_toclient == NULL ||
1886  !(pflow->sgh_toclient->flags & SIG_GROUP_HEAD_HAVEFILEMAGIC)))
1887  {
1888  SCLogDebug("disabling magic for flow");
1889  FileDisableMagic(pflow, STREAM_TOCLIENT);
1890  }
1891 
1892  /* check if this flow needs md5, if not disable it */
1893  if (!FileForceMd5() && (pflow->sgh_toclient == NULL ||
1894  !(pflow->sgh_toclient->flags & SIG_GROUP_HEAD_HAVEFILEMD5)))
1895  {
1896  SCLogDebug("disabling md5 for flow");
1897  FileDisableMd5(pflow, STREAM_TOCLIENT);
1898  }
1899 
1900  /* see if this sgh requires us to consider filesize */
1901  if (pflow->sgh_toclient == NULL ||
1902  !(pflow->sgh_toclient->flags & SIG_GROUP_HEAD_HAVEFILESIZE))
1903  {
1904  SCLogDebug("disabling filesize for flow");
1905  FileDisableFilesize(pflow, STREAM_TOCLIENT);
1906  }
1907  }
1908  }
1909 
1910  /* if we had no alerts that involved the smsgs,
1911  * we can get rid of them now. */
1912  StreamMsgReturnListToPool(smsg);
1913 
1914  FLOWLOCK_UNLOCK(pflow);
1915  }
1916  PACKET_PROFILING_DETECT_END(p, PROF_DETECT_CLEANUP);
1917 
1918  SCReturnInt((int)(alerts > 0));
1919 }
1920 
1921 /** \brief Apply action(s) and Set 'drop' sig info,
1922  * if applicable */
1923 void DetectSignatureApplyActions(Packet *p, const Signature *s)
1924 {
1925  PACKET_UPDATE_ACTION(p, s->action);
1926 
1927  if (s->action & ACTION_DROP) {
1928  if (p->alerts.drop.action == 0) {
1929  p->alerts.drop.num = s->num;
1930  p->alerts.drop.action = s->action;
1931  p->alerts.drop.s = (Signature *)s;
1932  }
1933  }
1934 }

1938 static DetectEngineThreadCtx *GetTenantById(HashTable *h, uint32_t id)
1939 {
1940  /* technically we need to pass a DetectEngineThreadCtx struct with the
1941  * tentant_id member. But as that member is the first in the struct, we
1942  * can use the id directly. */
1943  return HashTableLookup(h, &id, 0);
1944 }
1945 
1946 /** \brief Detection engine thread wrapper.
1947  * \param tv thread vars
1948  * \param p packet to inspect
1949  * \param data thread specific data
1950  * \param pq packet queue
1951  * \retval TM_ECODE_FAILED error
1952  * \retval TM_ECODE_OK ok
1953  */
1954 TmEcode Detect(ThreadVars *tv, Packet *p, void *data, PacketQueue *pq, PacketQueue *postpq)
1955 {
1956  DEBUG_VALIDATE_PACKET(p);
1957 
1958  /* No need to perform any detection on this packet, if the the given flag is set.*/
1959  if ((p->flags & PKT_NOPACKET_INSPECTION) ||
1960  (PACKET_TEST_ACTION(p, ACTION_DROP)))
1961  {
1962  /* hack: if we are in pass the entire flow mode, we need to still
1963  * update the inspect_id forward. So test for the condition here,
1964  * and call the update code if necessary. */
1965  if (p->flow) {
1966  uint8_t flags = 0;
1967  FLOWLOCK_RDLOCK(p->flow);
1968  int pass = ((p->flow->flags & FLOW_NOPACKET_INSPECTION));
1969  flags = FlowGetDisruptionFlags(p->flow, flags);
1970  AppProto alproto = FlowGetAppProtocol(p->flow);
1971  FLOWLOCK_UNLOCK(p->flow);
1972  if (pass && AppLayerParserProtocolSupportsTxs(p->proto, alproto)) {
1973  if (p->flowflags & FLOW_PKT_TOSERVER) {
1974  flags |= STREAM_TOSERVER;
1975  } else {
1976  flags |= STREAM_TOCLIENT;
1977  }
1978  DeStateUpdateInspectTransactionId(p->flow, flags);
1979  }
1980  }
1981  return 0;
1982  }
1983 
1984  DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx = NULL;
1985  DetectEngineThreadCtx *det_ctx = (DetectEngineThreadCtx *)data;
1986  if (det_ctx == NULL) {
1987  printf("ERROR: Detect has no thread ctx\n");
1988  goto error;
1989  }
1990 
1991  if (SC_ATOMIC_GET(det_ctx->so_far_used_by_detect) == 0) {
1992  (void)SC_ATOMIC_SET(det_ctx->so_far_used_by_detect, 1);
1993  SCLogDebug("Detect Engine using new det_ctx - %p",
1994  det_ctx);
1995  }
1996 
1997  if (det_ctx->TenantGetId != NULL) {
1998  /* in MT mode, but no tenants registered yet */
1999  if (det_ctx->mt_det_ctxs_cnt == 0) {
2000  return TM_ECODE_OK;
2001  }
2002 
2003  uint32_t tenant_id = p->tenant_id;
2004  if (tenant_id == 0)
2005  tenant_id = det_ctx->TenantGetId(det_ctx, p);
2006  if (tenant_id > 0 && tenant_id < det_ctx->mt_det_ctxs_cnt) {
2007  p->tenant_id = tenant_id;
2008  det_ctx = GetTenantById(det_ctx->mt_det_ctxs_hash, tenant_id);
2009  if (det_ctx == NULL)
2010  return TM_ECODE_OK;
2011  de_ctx = det_ctx->de_ctx;
2012  if (de_ctx == NULL)
2013  return TM_ECODE_OK;
2014 
2015  if (SC_ATOMIC_GET(det_ctx->so_far_used_by_detect) == 0) {
2016  (void)SC_ATOMIC_SET(det_ctx->so_far_used_by_detect, 1);
2017  SCLogDebug("MT de_ctx %p det_ctx %p (tenant %u)", de_ctx, det_ctx, tenant_id);
2018  }
2019  } else {
2020  return TM_ECODE_OK;
2021  }
2022  } else {
2023  de_ctx = det_ctx->de_ctx;
2024  }
2025 
2026  /* see if the packet matches one or more of the sigs */
2027  int r = SigMatchSignatures(tv,de_ctx,det_ctx,p);
2028  if (r >= 0) {
2029  return TM_ECODE_OK;
2030  }
2031 
2032 error:
2033  return TM_ECODE_FAILED;
2034 }
2035

2037 {
2038  return DetectEngineThreadCtxInit(t,initdata,data);
2039 }

2041 TmEcode DetectThreadDeinit(ThreadVars *t, void *data)
2042 {
2043  return DetectEngineThreadCtxDeinit(t,data);

2046 void SigCleanSignatures(DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx)
2047 {
2048  Signature *s = NULL, *ns;
2049 
2050  if (de_ctx == NULL)
2051  return;
2052 
2053  for (s = de_ctx->sig_list; s != NULL;) {
2054  ns = s->next;
2055  SigFree(s);
2056  s = ns;
2057  }
2058 
2059  de_ctx->sig_list = NULL;
2060 
2061  DetectEngineResetMaxSigId(de_ctx);
2062  de_ctx->sig_list = NULL;
2063 }
2064 
2065 /** \brief Find a specific signature by sid and gid
2066  * \param de_ctx detection engine ctx
2067  * \param sid the signature id
2068  * \param gid the signature group id
2069  *
2070  * \retval s sig found
2071  * \retval NULL sig not found
2072  */
2073 Signature *SigFindSignatureBySidGid(DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx, uint32_t sid, uint32_t gid)
2074 {
2075  Signature *s = NULL;
2076 
2077  if (de_ctx == NULL)
2078  return NULL;
2079 
2080  for (s = de_ctx->sig_list; s != NULL; s = s->next) {
2081  if (s->id == sid && s->gid == gid)
2082  return s;
2083  }
2084 
2085  return NULL;
2086 }

2090 {

2092  return 1;
2093 
2094  return 0;

2106 {
2107  if (s == NULL)
2108  return 0;
2109 
2110  if (s->flags & SIG_FLAG_FILESTORE)
2111  return 1;
2112 
2113  return 0;
2114 }

2123  */

2160  * \retval 1 yes
2161  */

2173 /** \brief Test is a initialized signature is IP only
2174  * \param de_ctx detection engine ctx
2175  * \param s the signature
2176  * \retval 1 sig is ip only
2177  * \retval 0 sig is not ip only
2178  */
2179 int SignatureIsIPOnly(DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx, Signature *s)
2180 {
2181  if (s->alproto != ALPROTO_UNKNOWN)
2182  return 0;
2183 
2184  if (s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_PMATCH] != NULL)
2185  return 0;
2186 
2187  if (s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_UMATCH] != NULL)
2188  return 0;
2189 
2190  if (s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HCBDMATCH] != NULL)
2191  return 0;
2192 
2193  if (s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_FILEDATA] != NULL)
2194  return 0;
2195 
2196  if (s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HHDMATCH] != NULL)
2197  return 0;
2198 
2199  if (s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HRHDMATCH] != NULL)
2200  return 0;
2201 
2202  if (s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HMDMATCH] != NULL)
2203  return 0;
2204 
2205  if (s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HCDMATCH] != NULL)
2206  return 0;
2207 
2208  if (s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HRUDMATCH] != NULL)
2209  return 0;
2210 
2211  if (s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HSMDMATCH] != NULL)
2212  return 0;
2213 
2214  if (s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HSCDMATCH] != NULL)
2215  return 0;
2216 
2217  if (s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HUADMATCH] != NULL)
2218  return 0;
2219 
2220  if (s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HHHDMATCH] != NULL)
2221  return 0;
2222 
2223  if (s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HRHHDMATCH] != NULL)
2224  return 0;
2225 
2226  if (s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_AMATCH] != NULL)
2227  return 0;
2228 
2229  /* TMATCH list can be ignored, it contains TAGs and
2230  * tags are compatible to IP-only. */
2231 
2232  IPOnlyCIDRItem *cidr_item;
2233  cidr_item = s->CidrSrc;
2234  while (cidr_item != NULL) {
2235  if (cidr_item->negated)
2236  return 0;
2237 
2238  cidr_item = cidr_item->next;
2239  }
2240  cidr_item = s->CidrDst;
2241  while (cidr_item != NULL) {
2242  if (cidr_item->negated)
2243  return 0;
2244 
2245  cidr_item = cidr_item->next;
2246  }
2247 
2248  SigMatch *sm = s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_MATCH];
2249  if (sm == NULL)
2250  goto iponly;
2251 
2252  for ( ; sm != NULL; sm = sm->next) {
2253  if ( !(sigmatch_table[sm->type].flags & SIGMATCH_IPONLY_COMPAT))
2254  return 0;
2255  /* we have enabled flowbits to be compatible with ip only sigs, as long
2256  * as the sig only has a "set" flowbits */
2257  if (sm->type == DETECT_FLOWBITS &&
2258  (((DetectFlowbitsData *)sm->ctx)->cmd != DETECT_FLOWBITS_CMD_SET) ) {
2259  return 0;
2260  }
2261  }
2262 
2263 iponly:
2264  if (!(de_ctx->flags & DE_QUIET)) {
2265  SCLogDebug("IP-ONLY (%" PRIu32 "): source %s, dest %s", s->id,
2266  s->flags & SIG_FLAG_SRC_ANY ? "ANY" : "SET",
2267  s->flags & SIG_FLAG_DST_ANY ? "ANY" : "SET");
2268  }
2269  return 1;
2270 }
2271 
2272 /**
2273  * \internal
2274  * \brief Check if the initialized signature is inspecting the packet payload
2275  * \param de_ctx detection engine ctx
2276  * \param s the signature
2277  * \retval 1 sig is inspecting the payload
2278  * \retval 0 sig is not inspecting the payload
2279  */
2280 static int SignatureIsInspectingPayload(DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx, Signature *s)
2281 {
2282 
2283  if (s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_PMATCH] != NULL) {
2284  return 1;
2285  }
2286 #if 0
2287  SigMatch *sm = s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_PMATCH];
2288  if (sm == NULL)
2289  return 0;
2290 
2291  for (; sm != NULL; sm = sm->next) {
2292  if (sigmatch_table[sm->type].flags & SIGMATCH_PAYLOAD) {
2293  if (!(de_ctx->flags & DE_QUIET))
2294  SCLogDebug("Signature (%" PRIu32 "): is inspecting payload.", s->id);
2295  return 1;
2296  }
2297  }
2298 #endif
2299  return 0;
2300 }
2301 
2302 /**
2303  * \internal
2304  * \brief check if a signature is decoder event matching only
2305  * \param de_ctx detection engine
2306  * \param s the signature to test
2307  * \retval 0 not a DEOnly sig
2308  * \retval 1 DEOnly sig
2309  */
2310 static int SignatureIsDEOnly(DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx, Signature *s)
2311 {
2312  if (s->alproto != ALPROTO_UNKNOWN) {
2313  SCReturnInt(0);
2314  }
2315 
2316  if (s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_PMATCH] != NULL ||
2317  s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_UMATCH] != NULL ||
2318  s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_AMATCH] != NULL ||
2319  s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HCBDMATCH] != NULL ||
2320  s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_FILEDATA] != NULL ||
2321  s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HHDMATCH] != NULL ||
2322  s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HRHDMATCH] != NULL ||
2323  s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HMDMATCH] != NULL ||
2324  s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HCDMATCH] != NULL ||
2325  s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HSMDMATCH] != NULL ||
2326  s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HSCDMATCH] != NULL ||
2327  s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HRUDMATCH] != NULL ||
2328  s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HUADMATCH] != NULL ||
2329  s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HHHDMATCH] != NULL ||
2330  s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HRHHDMATCH] != NULL)
2331  {
2332  SCReturnInt(0);
2333  }
2334 
2335  /* check for conflicting keywords */
2336  SigMatch *sm = s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_MATCH];
2337  for ( ;sm != NULL; sm = sm->next) {
2338  if ( !(sigmatch_table[sm->type].flags & SIGMATCH_DEONLY_COMPAT))
2339  SCReturnInt(0);
2340  }
2341 
2342  /* need at least one decode event keyword to be considered decode event. */
2343  sm = s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_MATCH];
2344  for ( ;sm != NULL; sm = sm->next) {
2345  if (sm->type == DETECT_DECODE_EVENT)
2346  goto deonly;
2347  if (sm->type == DETECT_ENGINE_EVENT)
2348  goto deonly;
2349  if (sm->type == DETECT_STREAM_EVENT)
2350  goto deonly;
2351  }
2352 
2353  SCReturnInt(0);
2354 
2355 deonly:
2356  if (!(de_ctx->flags & DE_QUIET)) {
2357  SCLogDebug("DE-ONLY (%" PRIu32 "): source %s, dest %s", s->id,
2358  s->flags & SIG_FLAG_SRC_ANY ? "ANY" : "SET",
2359  s->flags & SIG_FLAG_DST_ANY ? "ANY" : "SET");
2360  }
2361 
2362  SCReturnInt(1);
2363 }
2364 
2365 #define MASK_TCP_INITDEINIT_FLAGS (TH_SYN|TH_RST|TH_FIN)
2366 #define MASK_TCP_UNUSUAL_FLAGS (TH_URG|TH_ECN|TH_CWR)
2367 
2368 /* Create mask for this packet + it's flow if it has one
2369  *
2370  * Sets SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_PAYLOAD, SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_FLOW,
2371  * SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_HTTP_STATE, SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_DCE_STATE
2372  */
2373 static void
2374 PacketCreateMask(Packet *p, SignatureMask *mask, AppProto alproto, int has_state, StreamMsg *smsg,
2375  int app_decoder_events)
2376 {
2377  /* no payload inspect flag doesn't apply to smsg */
2378  if (smsg != NULL || (!(p->flags & PKT_NOPAYLOAD_INSPECTION) && p->payload_len > 0)) {
2379  SCLogDebug("packet has payload");
2380  (*mask) |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_PAYLOAD;
2381  } else {
2382  SCLogDebug("packet has no payload");
2383  (*mask) |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_NO_PAYLOAD;
2384  }
2385 
2386  if (p->events.cnt > 0 || app_decoder_events != 0 || p->app_layer_events != NULL) {
2387  SCLogDebug("packet/flow has events set");
2388  (*mask) |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_ENGINE_EVENT;
2389  }
2390 
2391  if (PKT_IS_TCP(p)) {
2392  if ((p->tcph->th_flags & MASK_TCP_INITDEINIT_FLAGS) != 0) {
2393  (*mask) |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_FLAGS_INITDEINIT;
2394  }
2395  if ((p->tcph->th_flags & MASK_TCP_UNUSUAL_FLAGS) != 0) {
2396  (*mask) |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_FLAGS_UNUSUAL;
2397  }
2398  }
2399 
2400  if (p->flags & PKT_HAS_FLOW) {
2401  SCLogDebug("packet has flow");
2402  (*mask) |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_FLOW;
2403 
2404  if (has_state) {
2405  switch(alproto) {
2406  case ALPROTO_HTTP:
2407  SCLogDebug("packet/flow has http state");
2408  (*mask) |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_HTTP_STATE;
2409  break;
2410  case ALPROTO_SMB:
2411  case ALPROTO_SMB2:
2412  case ALPROTO_DCERPC:
2413  SCLogDebug("packet/flow has dce state");
2414  (*mask) |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_DCE_STATE;
2415  break;
2416  case ALPROTO_SSH:
2417  SCLogDebug("packet/flow has ssh state");
2418  (*mask) |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_SSH_STATE;
2419  break;
2420  case ALPROTO_TLS:
2421  SCLogDebug("packet/flow has tls state");
2422  (*mask) |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_TLS_STATE;
2423  break;
2424  case ALPROTO_DNS:
2425  SCLogDebug("packet/flow has dns state");
2426  (*mask) |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_DNS_STATE;
2427  break;
2428  case ALPROTO_FTP:
2429  SCLogDebug("packet/flow has ftp state");
2430  (*mask) |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_FTP_STATE;
2431  break;
2432  case ALPROTO_SMTP:
2433  SCLogDebug("packet/flow has smtp state");
2434  (*mask) |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_SMTP_STATE;
2435  break;
2436  case ALPROTO_TEMPLATE:
2437  SCLogDebug("packet/flow has template state");
2438  (*mask) |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_TEMPLATE_STATE;
2439  break;
2440  default:
2441  SCLogDebug("packet/flow has other state");
2442  break;
2443  }
2444  } else {
2445  SCLogDebug("no alstate");
2446  }
2447  }
2448 }
2449 
2450 static int SignatureCreateMask(Signature *s)
2451 {
2452  SCEnter();
2453 
2454  if (s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_PMATCH] != NULL) {
2455  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_PAYLOAD;
2456  SCLogDebug("sig requires payload");
2457  }
2458 
2459  if (s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_DMATCH] != NULL) {
2460  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_DCE_STATE;
2461  SCLogDebug("sig requires dce state");
2462  }
2463 
2464  if (s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_UMATCH] != NULL) {
2465  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_HTTP_STATE;
2466  SCLogDebug("sig requires http state");
2467  }
2468 
2469  if (s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HCBDMATCH] != NULL) {
2470  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_HTTP_STATE;
2471  SCLogDebug("sig requires http app state");
2472  }
2473 
2474  if (s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_FILEDATA] != NULL) {
2475  /* set the state depending from the protocol */
2476  if (s->alproto == ALPROTO_HTTP)
2477  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_HTTP_STATE;
2478  else if (s->alproto == ALPROTO_SMTP)
2479  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_SMTP_STATE;
2480 
2481  SCLogDebug("sig requires http or smtp app state");
2482  }
2483 
2484  if (s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HHDMATCH] != NULL) {
2485  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_HTTP_STATE;
2486  SCLogDebug("sig requires http app state");
2487  }
2488 
2489  if (s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HRHDMATCH] != NULL) {
2490  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_HTTP_STATE;
2491  SCLogDebug("sig requires http app state");
2492  }
2493 
2494  if (s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HMDMATCH] != NULL) {
2495  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_HTTP_STATE;
2496  SCLogDebug("sig requires http app state");
2497  }
2498 
2499  if (s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HCDMATCH] != NULL) {
2500  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_HTTP_STATE;
2501  SCLogDebug("sig requires http app state");
2502  }
2503 
2504  if (s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HRUDMATCH] != NULL) {
2505  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_HTTP_STATE;
2506  SCLogDebug("sig requires http app state");
2507  }
2508 
2509  if (s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HSMDMATCH] != NULL) {
2510  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_HTTP_STATE;
2511  SCLogDebug("sig requires http app state");
2512  }
2513 
2514  if (s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HSCDMATCH] != NULL) {
2515  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_HTTP_STATE;
2516  SCLogDebug("sig requires http app state");
2517  }
2518 
2519  if (s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HUADMATCH] != NULL) {
2520  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_HTTP_STATE;
2521  SCLogDebug("sig requires http app state");
2522  }
2523 
2524  if (s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HHHDMATCH] != NULL) {
2525  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_HTTP_STATE;
2526  SCLogDebug("sig requires http app state");
2527  }
2528 
2529  if (s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_HRHHDMATCH] != NULL) {
2530  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_HTTP_STATE;
2531  SCLogDebug("sig requires http app state");
2532  }
2533 
2534  SigMatch *sm;
2535  for (sm = s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_AMATCH] ; sm != NULL; sm = sm->next) {
2536  switch(sm->type) {
2537  case DETECT_AL_URILEN:
2538  case DETECT_AL_HTTP_URI:
2539  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_HTTP_STATE;
2540  SCLogDebug("sig requires dce http state");
2541  break;
2542  case DETECT_AL_APP_LAYER_EVENT:
2543  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_ENGINE_EVENT;
2544  break;
2545  }
2546  }
2547 
2548  for (sm = s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_APP_EVENT] ; sm != NULL; sm = sm->next) {
2549  switch (sm->type) {
2550  case DETECT_AL_APP_LAYER_EVENT:
2551  {
2552  DetectAppLayerEventData *aed = (DetectAppLayerEventData *)sm->ctx;
2553  switch (aed->alproto) {
2554  case ALPROTO_HTTP:
2555  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_HTTP_STATE;
2556  SCLogDebug("sig %u requires http app state (http event)", s->id);
2557  break;
2558  case ALPROTO_SMTP:
2559  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_SMTP_STATE;
2560  SCLogDebug("sig %u requires smtp app state (smtp event)", s->id);
2561  break;
2562  case ALPROTO_DNS:
2563  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_DNS_STATE;
2564  SCLogDebug("sig %u requires dns app state (dns event)", s->id);
2565  break;
2566  }
2567  break;
2568  }
2569  }
2570  }
2571 
2572  for (sm = s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_MATCH] ; sm != NULL; sm = sm->next) {
2573  switch(sm->type) {
2574  case DETECT_FLOWBITS:
2575  {
2576  /* figure out what flowbit action */
2577  DetectFlowbitsData *fb = (DetectFlowbitsData *)sm->ctx;
2578  if (fb->cmd == DETECT_FLOWBITS_CMD_ISSET) {
2579  /* not a mask flag, but still set it here */
2580  s->flags |= SIG_FLAG_REQUIRE_FLOWVAR;
2581 
2582  SCLogDebug("SIG_FLAG_REQUIRE_FLOWVAR set as sig has "
2583  "flowbit isset option.");
2584  }
2585 
2586  /* flow is required for any flowbit manipulation */
2587  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_FLOW;
2588  SCLogDebug("sig requires flow to be able to manipulate "
2589  "flowbit(s)");
2590  break;
2591  }
2592  case DETECT_FLAGS:
2593  {
2594  DetectFlagsData *fl = (DetectFlagsData *)sm->ctx;
2595 
2596  if (fl->flags & TH_SYN) {
2597  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_FLAGS_INITDEINIT;
2598  SCLogDebug("sig requires SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_FLAGS_INITDEINIT");
2599  }
2600  if (fl->flags & TH_RST) {
2601  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_FLAGS_INITDEINIT;
2602  SCLogDebug("sig requires SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_FLAGS_INITDEINIT");
2603  }
2604  if (fl->flags & TH_FIN) {
2605  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_FLAGS_INITDEINIT;
2606  SCLogDebug("sig requires SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_FLAGS_INITDEINIT");
2607  }
2608  if (fl->flags & TH_URG) {
2609  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_FLAGS_UNUSUAL;
2610  SCLogDebug("sig requires SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_FLAGS_UNUSUAL");
2611  }
2612  if (fl->flags & TH_ECN) {
2613  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_FLAGS_UNUSUAL;
2614  SCLogDebug("sig requires SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_FLAGS_UNUSUAL");
2615  }
2616  if (fl->flags & TH_CWR) {
2617  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_FLAGS_UNUSUAL;
2618  SCLogDebug("sig requires SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_FLAGS_UNUSUAL");
2619  }
2620  break;
2621  }
2622  case DETECT_DSIZE:
2623  {
2624  DetectDsizeData *ds = (DetectDsizeData *)sm->ctx;
2625  switch (ds->mode) {
2626  case DETECTDSIZE_LT:
2627  /* LT will include 0, so no payload.
2628  * if GT is used in the same rule the
2629  * flag will be set anyway. */
2630  break;
2631  case DETECTDSIZE_RA:
2632  case DETECTDSIZE_GT:
2633  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_PAYLOAD;
2634  SCLogDebug("sig requires payload");
2635  break;
2636  case DETECTDSIZE_EQ:
2637  if (ds->dsize > 0) {
2638  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_PAYLOAD;
2639  SCLogDebug("sig requires payload");
2640  } else if (ds->dsize == 0) {
2641  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_NO_PAYLOAD;
2642  SCLogDebug("sig requires no payload");
2643  }
2644  break;
2645  }
2646  break;
2647  }
2648  case DETECT_AL_APP_LAYER_EVENT:
2649  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_ENGINE_EVENT;
2650  break;
2651  case DETECT_ENGINE_EVENT:
2652  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_ENGINE_EVENT;
2653  break;
2654  }
2655  }
2656 
2657  if (s->alproto == ALPROTO_SSH) {
2658  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_SSH_STATE;
2659  SCLogDebug("sig requires ssh state");
2660  }
2661  if (s->alproto == ALPROTO_TLS) {
2662  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_TLS_STATE;
2663  SCLogDebug("sig requires tls state");
2664  }
2665  if (s->alproto == ALPROTO_DNS) {
2666  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_DNS_STATE;
2667  SCLogDebug("sig requires dns state");
2668  }
2669  if (s->alproto == ALPROTO_FTP) {
2670  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_FTP_STATE;
2671  SCLogDebug("sig requires ftp state");
2672  }
2673  if (s->alproto == ALPROTO_SMTP) {
2674  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_SMTP_STATE;
2675  SCLogDebug("sig requires smtp state");
2676  }
2677  if (s->alproto == ALPROTO_TEMPLATE) {
2678  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_TEMPLATE_STATE;
2679  SCLogDebug("sig requires template state");
2680  }
2681 
2682  if ((s->mask & SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_DCE_STATE) ||
2683  (s->mask & SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_HTTP_STATE) ||
2684  (s->mask & SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_SSH_STATE) ||
2685  (s->mask & SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_DNS_STATE) ||
2686  (s->mask & SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_FTP_STATE) ||
2687  (s->mask & SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_SMTP_STATE) ||
2688  (s->mask & SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_TEMPLATE_STATE) ||
2689  (s->mask & SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_TLS_STATE))
2690  {
2691  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_FLOW;
2692  SCLogDebug("sig requires flow");
2693  }
2694 
2695  if (s->init_flags & SIG_FLAG_INIT_FLOW) {
2696  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_FLOW;
2697  SCLogDebug("sig requires flow");
2698  }
2699 
2700  if (s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_AMATCH] != NULL) {
2701  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_FLOW;
2702  SCLogDebug("sig requires flow");
2703  }
2704 
2705  if (s->flags & SIG_FLAG_APPLAYER) {
2706  s->mask |= SIG_MASK_REQUIRE_FLOW;
2707  SCLogDebug("sig requires flow");
2708  }
2709 
2710  SCLogDebug("mask %02X", s->mask);
2711  SCReturnInt(0);
2712 }
