2775 
2776 /** \brief get max dsize "depth"
2777  * \param s signature to get dsize value from
2778  * \retval depth or negative value
2779  */
2780 static int SigParseGetMaxDsize(Signature *s)
2781 {
2782  if (s->flags & SIG_FLAG_DSIZE && s->dsize_sm != NULL) {
2783  DetectDsizeData *dd = (DetectDsizeData *)s->dsize_sm->ctx;
2784 
2785  switch (dd->mode) {
2786  case DETECTDSIZE_LT:
2787  case DETECTDSIZE_EQ:
2788  return dd->dsize;
2789  case DETECTDSIZE_RA:
2790  return dd->dsize2;
2791  case DETECTDSIZE_GT:
2792  default:
2793  SCReturnInt(-2);
2794  }
2795  }
2796  SCReturnInt(-1);
2797 }
2798 
2799 /** \brief set prefilter dsize pair
2800  * \param s signature to get dsize value from
2801  */
2802 static void SigParseSetDsizePair(Signature *s)
2803 {
2804  if (s->flags & SIG_FLAG_DSIZE && s->dsize_sm != NULL) {
2805  DetectDsizeData *dd = (DetectDsizeData *)s->dsize_sm->ctx;
2806 
2807  uint16_t low = 0;
2808  uint16_t high = 65535;
2809 
2810  switch (dd->mode) {
2811  case DETECTDSIZE_LT:
2812  low = 0;
2813  high = dd->dsize;
2814  break;
2815  case DETECTDSIZE_EQ:
2816  low = dd->dsize;
2817  high = dd->dsize;
2818  break;
2819  case DETECTDSIZE_RA:
2820  low = dd->dsize;
2821  high = dd->dsize2;
2822  break;
2823  case DETECTDSIZE_GT:
2824  low = dd->dsize;
2825  high = 65535;
2826  break;
2827  }
2828  s->dsize_low = low;
2829  s->dsize_high = high;
2830 
2831  SCLogDebug("low %u, high %u", low, high);
2832  }
2833 }
2834 
2835 /**
2836  * \brief Apply dsize as depth to content matches in the rule
2837  * \param s signature to get dsize value from
2838  */
2839 static void SigParseApplyDsizeToContent(Signature *s)
2840 {
2841  SCEnter();
2842 
2843  if (s->flags & SIG_FLAG_DSIZE) {
2844  SigParseSetDsizePair(s);
2845 
2846  int dsize = SigParseGetMaxDsize(s);
2847  if (dsize < 0) {
2848  /* nothing to do */
2849  return;
2850  }
2851 
2852  SigMatch *sm = s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_PMATCH];
2853  for ( ; sm != NULL; sm = sm->next) {
2854  if (sm->type != DETECT_CONTENT) {
2855  continue;
2856  }
2857 
2858  DetectContentData *cd = (DetectContentData *)sm->ctx;
2859  if (cd == NULL) {
2860  continue;
2861  }
2862 
2863  if (cd->depth == 0 || cd->depth >= dsize) {
2864  cd->depth = (uint16_t)dsize;
2865  SCLogDebug("updated %u, content %u to have depth %u "
2866  "because of dsize.", s->id, cd->id, cd->depth);
2867  }
2868  }
2869  }
2870 }
2871 
2872 /**
2873  * \brief Preprocess signature, classify ip-only, etc, build sig array
2874  *
2875  * \param de_ctx Pointer to the Detection Engine Context
2876  *
2877  * \retval 0 on success
2878  * \retval -1 on failure
2879  */
2880 int SigAddressPrepareStage1(DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx)
2881 {
2882  Signature *tmp_s = NULL;
2883  uint32_t cnt_iponly = 0;
2884  uint32_t cnt_payload = 0;
2885  uint32_t cnt_applayer = 0;
2886  uint32_t cnt_deonly = 0;
2887 
2888  //DetectAddressPrintMemory();
2889  //DetectSigGroupPrintMemory();
2890  //DetectPortPrintMemory();
2891 
2892  if (!(de_ctx->flags & DE_QUIET)) {
2893  SCLogDebug("building signature grouping structure, stage 1: "
2894  "preprocessing rules...");
2895  }
2896 
2897 #ifdef HAVE_LUAJIT
2898  /* run this before the mpm states are initialized */
2899  if (DetectLuajitSetupStatesPool(de_ctx->detect_luajit_instances, TRUE) != 0) {
2900  if (de_ctx->failure_fatal)
2901  return -1;
2902  }
2903 #endif
2904 
2905  de_ctx->sig_array_len = DetectEngineGetMaxSigId(de_ctx);
2906  de_ctx->sig_array_size = (de_ctx->sig_array_len * sizeof(Signature *));
2907  de_ctx->sig_array = (Signature **)SCMalloc(de_ctx->sig_array_size);
2908  if (de_ctx->sig_array == NULL)
2909  goto error;
2910  memset(de_ctx->sig_array,0,de_ctx->sig_array_size);
2911 
2912  SCLogDebug("signature lookup array: %" PRIu32 " sigs, %" PRIu32 " bytes",
2913  de_ctx->sig_array_len, de_ctx->sig_array_size);
2914 
2915  /* now for every rule add the source group */
2916  for (tmp_s = de_ctx->sig_list; tmp_s != NULL; tmp_s = tmp_s->next) {
2917  de_ctx->sig_array[tmp_s->num] = tmp_s;
2918 
2919  SCLogDebug("Signature %" PRIu32 ", internal id %" PRIu32 ", ptrs %p %p ", tmp_s->id, tmp_s->num, tmp_s, de_ctx->sig_array[tmp_s->num]);
2920 
2921  /* see if the sig is ip only */
2922  if (SignatureIsIPOnly(de_ctx, tmp_s) == 1) {
2923  tmp_s->flags |= SIG_FLAG_IPONLY;
2924  cnt_iponly++;
2925 
2926  SCLogDebug("Signature %"PRIu32" is considered \"IP only\"", tmp_s->id);
2927 
2928  /* see if any sig is inspecting the packet payload */
2929  } else if (SignatureIsInspectingPayload(de_ctx, tmp_s) == 1) {
2930  tmp_s->init_flags |= SIG_FLAG_INIT_PAYLOAD;
2931  cnt_payload++;
2932 
2933  SCLogDebug("Signature %"PRIu32" is considered \"Payload inspecting\"", tmp_s->id);
2934  } else if (SignatureIsDEOnly(de_ctx, tmp_s) == 1) {
2935  tmp_s->init_flags |= SIG_FLAG_INIT_DEONLY;
2936  SCLogDebug("Signature %"PRIu32" is considered \"Decoder Event only\"", tmp_s->id);
2937  cnt_deonly++;
2938  }
2939 
2940  if (tmp_s->flags & SIG_FLAG_APPLAYER) {
2941  SCLogDebug("Signature %"PRIu32" is considered \"Applayer inspecting\"", tmp_s->id);
2942  cnt_applayer++;
2943  }
2944 
2945 #ifdef DEBUG
2946  if (SCLogDebugEnabled()) {
2947  uint16_t colen = 0;
2948  char copresent = 0;
2949  SigMatch *sm;
2950  DetectContentData *co;
2951  for (sm = tmp_s->sm_lists[DETECT_SM_LIST_MATCH]; sm != NULL; sm = sm->next) {
2952  if (sm->type != DETECT_CONTENT)
2953  continue;
2954 
2955  copresent = 1;
2956  co = (DetectContentData *)sm->ctx;
2957  if (co->content_len > colen)
2958  colen = co->content_len;
2959  }
2960 
2961  if (copresent && colen == 1) {
2962  SCLogDebug("signature %8u content maxlen 1", tmp_s->id);
2963  int proto;
2964  for (proto = 0; proto < 256; proto++) {
2965  if (tmp_s->proto.proto[(proto/8)] & (1<<(proto%8)))
2966  SCLogDebug("=> proto %" PRId32 "", proto);
2967  }
2968  }
2969  }
2970 #endif /* DEBUG */
2971 
2972  SignatureCreateMask(tmp_s);
2973  SigParseApplyDsizeToContent(tmp_s);
2974 
2975  de_ctx->sig_cnt++;
2976  }
2977 
2978  //DetectAddressPrintMemory();
2979  //DetectSigGroupPrintMemory();
2980  //DetectPortPrintMemory();
2981 
2982  if (!(de_ctx->flags & DE_QUIET)) {
2983  SCLogInfo("%" PRIu32 " signatures processed. %" PRIu32 " are IP-only "
2984  "rules, %" PRIu32 " are inspecting packet payload, %"PRIu32
2985  " inspect application layer, %"PRIu32" are decoder event only",
2986  de_ctx->sig_cnt, cnt_iponly, cnt_payload, cnt_applayer,
2987  cnt_deonly);
2988 
2989  SCLogInfo("building signature grouping structure, stage 1: "
2990  "preprocessing rules... complete");
2991  }
2992  return 0;
2993 
2994 error:
2995  return -1;
2996 }

2998 static int DetectEngineLookupBuildSourceAddressList(DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx, DetectEngineLookupFlow *flow_gh, Signature *s, int family)
2999 {
3000  DetectAddress *gr = NULL, *lookup_gr = NULL, *head = NULL;
3001  int proto;
3002 
3003  if (family == AF_INET) {
3004  head = s->src.ipv4_head;
3005  } else if (family == AF_INET6) {
3006  head = s->src.ipv6_head;
3007  } else {
3008  head = s->src.any_head;
3009  }
3010 
3011  /* for each source address group in the signature... */
3012  for (gr = head; gr != NULL; gr = gr->next) {
3013  BUG_ON(gr->ip.family == 0 && !(gr->flags & ADDRESS_FLAG_ANY));
3014 
3015  /* ...and each protocol the signature matches on... */
3016  for (proto = 0; proto < 256; proto++) {
3017  if ((s->proto.proto[(proto/8)] & (1<<(proto%8))) || (s->proto.flags & DETECT_PROTO_ANY)) {
3018  /* ...see if the group is in the tmp list, and if not add it. */
3019  if (family == AF_INET) {
3020  lookup_gr = DetectAddressLookupInList(flow_gh->tmp_gh[proto]->ipv4_head,gr);
3021  } else if (family == AF_INET6) {
3022  lookup_gr = DetectAddressLookupInList(flow_gh->tmp_gh[proto]->ipv6_head,gr);
3023  } else {
3024  lookup_gr = DetectAddressLookupInList(flow_gh->tmp_gh[proto]->any_head,gr);
3025  }
3026 
3027  if (lookup_gr == NULL) {
3028  DetectAddress *grtmp = DetectAddressCopy(gr);
3029  if (grtmp == NULL) {
3030  goto error;
3031  }
3032  SigGroupHeadAppendSig(de_ctx, &grtmp->sh, s);
3033 
3034  /* add to the lookup list */
3035  if (family == AF_INET) {
3036  DetectAddressAdd(&flow_gh->tmp_gh[proto]->ipv4_head, grtmp);
3037  } else if (family == AF_INET6) {
3038  DetectAddressAdd(&flow_gh->tmp_gh[proto]->ipv6_head, grtmp);
3039  } else {
3040  DetectAddressAdd(&flow_gh->tmp_gh[proto]->any_head, grtmp);
3041  }
3042  } else {
3043  /* our group will only have one sig, this one. So add that. */
3044  SigGroupHeadAppendSig(de_ctx, &lookup_gr->sh, s);
3045  lookup_gr->cnt++;
3046  }
3047  }
3048  }
3049  }
3050 
3051  return 0;
3052 error:
3053  return -1;
3054 }

3057  * \brief add signature to the right flow group(s)
3058  */
3059 static int DetectEngineLookupFlowAddSig(DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx, Signature *s, int family)
3060 {
3061  SCLogDebug("s->id %u", s->id);
3062 
3063  if (s->flags & SIG_FLAG_TOCLIENT) {
3064  SCLogDebug("s->id %u (toclient)", s->id);
3065  DetectEngineLookupBuildSourceAddressList(de_ctx,
3066  &de_ctx->flow_gh[0], s, family);
3067  }
3068 
3069  if (s->flags & SIG_FLAG_TOSERVER) {
3070  SCLogDebug("s->id %u (toserver)", s->id);
3071  DetectEngineLookupBuildSourceAddressList(de_ctx,
3072  &de_ctx->flow_gh[1], s, family);
3073  }
3074 
3075  return 0;
3076 }

3121 /* set unique_groups to 0 for no grouping.
3122  *
3123  * srchead is a ordered "inserted" list w/o internal overlap
3124  *
3125  */
3126 int CreateGroupedAddrList(DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx, DetectAddress *srchead,
3127  int family, DetectAddressHead *newhead,
3128  uint32_t unique_groups,
3129  int (*CompareFunc)(DetectAddress *, DetectAddress *),
3130  uint32_t max_idx)
3131 {
3132  DetectAddress *tmplist = NULL, *tmplist2 = NULL, *joingr = NULL;
3133  char insert = 0;
3134  DetectAddress *gr, *next_gr;
3135  uint32_t groups = 0;
3136 
3137  /* insert the addresses into the tmplist, where it will
3138  * be sorted descending on 'cnt'. */
3139  for (gr = srchead; gr != NULL; gr = gr->next) {
3140  BUG_ON(gr->ip.family == 0 && !(gr->flags & ADDRESS_FLAG_ANY));
3141 
3142  if (SMALL_MPM(gr->sh->mpm_content_minlen) && unique_groups > 0)
3143  unique_groups++;
3144 
3145  groups++;
3146 
3147  /* alloc a copy */
3148  DetectAddress *newtmp = DetectAddressCopy(gr);
3149  if (newtmp == NULL) {
3150  goto error;
3151  }
3152  SigGroupHeadCopySigs(de_ctx, gr->sh,&newtmp->sh);
3153 
3154  DetectPort *port = gr->port;
3155  for ( ; port != NULL; port = port->next) {
3156  DetectPortInsertCopy(de_ctx,&newtmp->port, port);
3157  newtmp->flags |= ADDRESS_HAVEPORT;
3158  }
3159 
3160  /* insert it */
3161  DetectAddress *tmpgr = tmplist, *prevtmpgr = NULL;
3162  if (tmplist == NULL) {
3163  /* empty list, set head */
3164  tmplist = newtmp;
3165  } else {
3166  /* look for the place to insert */
3167  for ( ; tmpgr != NULL&&!insert; tmpgr = tmpgr->next) {
3168  if (CompareFunc(gr, tmpgr)) {
3169  if (tmpgr == tmplist) {
3170  newtmp->next = tmplist;
3171  tmplist = newtmp;
3172  } else {
3173  newtmp->next = prevtmpgr->next;
3174  prevtmpgr->next = newtmp;
3175  }
3176  insert = 1;
3177  }
3178  prevtmpgr = tmpgr;
3179  }
3180  if (insert == 0) {
3181  newtmp->next = NULL;
3182  prevtmpgr->next = newtmp;
3183  }
3184  insert = 0;
3185  }
3186  }
3187 
3188  uint32_t i = unique_groups;
3189  if (i == 0) i = groups;
3190 
3191  for (gr = tmplist; gr != NULL; ) {
3192  BUG_ON(gr->ip.family == 0 && !(gr->flags & ADDRESS_FLAG_ANY));
3193 
3194  if (i == 0) {
3195  if (joingr == NULL) {
3196  joingr = DetectAddressCopy(gr);
3197  if (joingr == NULL) {
3198  goto error;
3199  }
3200 
3201  SigGroupHeadCopySigs(de_ctx,gr->sh,&joingr->sh);
3202 
3203  DetectPort *port = gr->port;
3204  for ( ; port != NULL; port = port->next) {
3205  DetectPortInsertCopy(de_ctx,&joingr->port, port);
3206  joingr->flags |= ADDRESS_HAVEPORT;
3207  }
3208  } else {
3209  DetectAddressJoin(de_ctx, joingr, gr);
3210  }
3211  } else {
3212  DetectAddress *newtmp = DetectAddressCopy(gr);
3213  if (newtmp == NULL) {
3214  goto error;
3215  }
3216 
3217  SigGroupHeadCopySigs(de_ctx,gr->sh,&newtmp->sh);
3218 
3219  DetectPort *port = gr->port;
3220  for ( ; port != NULL; port = port->next) {
3221  DetectPortInsertCopy(de_ctx,&newtmp->port, port);
3222  newtmp->flags |= ADDRESS_HAVEPORT;
3223  }
3224 
3225  if (tmplist2 == NULL) {
3226  tmplist2 = newtmp;
3227  } else {
3228  newtmp->next = tmplist2;
3229  tmplist2 = newtmp;
3230  }
3231  }
3232  if (i)i--;
3233 
3234  next_gr = gr->next;
3235  DetectAddressFree(gr);
3236  gr = next_gr;
3237  }
3238 
3239  /* we now have a tmplist2 containing the 'unique' groups and
3240  * possibly a joingr that covers the rest. Now build the newhead
3241  * that we will pass back to the caller.
3242  *
3243  * Start with inserting the unique groups */
3244  for (gr = tmplist2; gr != NULL; ) {
3245  BUG_ON(gr->ip.family == 0 && !(gr->flags & ADDRESS_FLAG_ANY));
3246 
3247  DetectAddress *newtmp = DetectAddressCopy(gr);
3248  if (newtmp == NULL) {
3249  goto error;
3250  }
3251  SigGroupHeadCopySigs(de_ctx, gr->sh,&newtmp->sh);
3252 
3253  DetectPort *port = gr->port;
3254  for ( ; port != NULL; port = port->next) {
3255  DetectPortInsertCopy(de_ctx, &newtmp->port, port);
3256  newtmp->flags |= ADDRESS_HAVEPORT;
3257  }
3258 
3259  DetectAddressInsert(de_ctx, newhead, newtmp);
3260 
3261  next_gr = gr->next;
3262  DetectAddressFree(gr);
3263  gr = next_gr;
3264  }
3265 
3266  /* if present, insert the joingr that covers the rest */
3267  if (joingr != NULL) {
3268  DetectAddressInsert(de_ctx, newhead, joingr);
3269  }
3270 
3271  return 0;
3272 error:
3273  return -1;
3274 }

3414  BUG_ON(r == -1);
3415 
3416  next_gr = gr->next;
3417  gr->next = NULL;
3418  DetectPortFree(gr);
3419  gr = next_gr;
3420  }
3421 
3422  DetectPortPrintList(*newhead);
3423 
3424  /* if present, insert the joingr that covers the rest */
3425  if (joingr != NULL) {
3426  SCLogDebug("inserting joingr %p", joingr);
3427  DetectPortInsert(de_ctx,newhead,joingr);
3428  } else {
3429  SCLogDebug("no joingr");
3430  }
3431 
3432  return 0;
3433 error:
3434  return -1;
3435 }
3436 
3437 /**
3438  * \internal
3439  * \brief add a decoder event signature to the detection engine ctx
3440  */
3441 static void DetectEngineAddDecoderEventSig(DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx, Signature *s)
3442 {
3443  SCLogDebug("adding signature %"PRIu32" to the decoder event sgh", s->id);
3444  SigGroupHeadAppendSig(de_ctx, &de_ctx->decoder_event_sgh, s);
3445 }
3446 
3447 /**
3448  * \brief Fill the global src group head, with the sigs included
3449  *
3450  * \param de_ctx Pointer to the Detection Engine Context whose Signatures have
3451  * to be processed
3452  *
3453  * \retval 0 On success
3454  * \retval -1 On failure
3455  */
3456 int SigAddressPrepareStage2(DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx)
3457 {
3458  Signature *tmp_s = NULL;
3459  uint32_t sigs = 0;
3460 
3461  if (!(de_ctx->flags & DE_QUIET)) {
3462  SCLogDebug("building signature grouping structure, stage 2: "
3463  "building source address lists...");
3464  }
3465 
3466  IPOnlyInit(de_ctx, &de_ctx->io_ctx);
3467 
3468  int f, proto;
3469  for (f = 0; f < FLOW_STATES; f++) {
3470  for (proto = 0; proto < 256; proto++) {
3471  de_ctx->flow_gh[f].src_gh[proto] = DetectAddressHeadInit();
3472  if (de_ctx->flow_gh[f].src_gh[proto] == NULL) {
3473  goto error;
3474  }
3475  de_ctx->flow_gh[f].tmp_gh[proto] = DetectAddressHeadInit();
3476  if (de_ctx->flow_gh[f].tmp_gh[proto] == NULL) {
3477  goto error;
3478  }
3479  }
3480  }
3481 
3482  /* now for every rule add the source group to our temp lists */
3483  for (tmp_s = de_ctx->sig_list; tmp_s != NULL; tmp_s = tmp_s->next) {
3484  SCLogDebug("tmp_s->id %"PRIu32, tmp_s->id);
3485  if (tmp_s->flags & SIG_FLAG_IPONLY) {
3486  IPOnlyAddSignature(de_ctx, &de_ctx->io_ctx, tmp_s);
3487  } else {
3488  DetectEngineLookupFlowAddSig(de_ctx, tmp_s, AF_INET);
3489  DetectEngineLookupFlowAddSig(de_ctx, tmp_s, AF_INET6);
3490  DetectEngineLookupFlowAddSig(de_ctx, tmp_s, AF_UNSPEC);
3491  }
3492 
3493  if (tmp_s->init_flags & SIG_FLAG_INIT_DEONLY) {
3494  DetectEngineAddDecoderEventSig(de_ctx, tmp_s);
3495  }
3496 
3497  sigs++;
3498  }
3499 
3500  /* create the final src addr list based on the tmplist. */
3501  for (f = 0; f < FLOW_STATES; f++) {
3502  for (proto = 0; proto < 256; proto++) {
3503  int groups = (f ? de_ctx->max_uniq_toserver_src_groups : de_ctx->max_uniq_toclient_src_groups);
3504 
3505  CreateGroupedAddrList(de_ctx,
3506  de_ctx->flow_gh[f].tmp_gh[proto]->ipv4_head, AF_INET,
3507  de_ctx->flow_gh[f].src_gh[proto], groups,
3508  CreateGroupedAddrListCmpMpmMinlen, DetectEngineGetMaxSigId(de_ctx));
3509 
3510  CreateGroupedAddrList(de_ctx,
3511  de_ctx->flow_gh[f].tmp_gh[proto]->ipv6_head, AF_INET6,
3512  de_ctx->flow_gh[f].src_gh[proto], groups,
3513  CreateGroupedAddrListCmpMpmMinlen, DetectEngineGetMaxSigId(de_ctx));
3514  CreateGroupedAddrList(de_ctx,
3515  de_ctx->flow_gh[f].tmp_gh[proto]->any_head, AF_UNSPEC,
3516  de_ctx->flow_gh[f].src_gh[proto], groups,
3517  CreateGroupedAddrListCmpMpmMinlen, DetectEngineGetMaxSigId(de_ctx));
3518 
3519  DetectAddressHeadFree(de_ctx->flow_gh[f].tmp_gh[proto]);
3520  de_ctx->flow_gh[f].tmp_gh[proto] = NULL;
3521  }
3522  }
3523  //DetectAddressPrintMemory();
3524  //DetectSigGroupPrintMemory();
3525 
3526  //printf("g_src_gh strt\n");
3527  //DetectAddressPrintList(g_src_gh->ipv4_head);
3528  //printf("g_src_gh end\n");
3529 
3530  IPOnlyPrepare(de_ctx);
3531  IPOnlyPrint(de_ctx, &de_ctx->io_ctx);
3532 #ifdef DEBUG
3533  DetectAddress *gr = NULL;
3534  if (!(de_ctx->flags & DE_QUIET)) {
3535  SCLogDebug("%" PRIu32 " total signatures:", sigs);
3536  }
3537 
3538  /* TCP */
3539  uint32_t cnt_any = 0, cnt_ipv4 = 0, cnt_ipv6 = 0;
3540  for (f = 0; f < FLOW_STATES; f++) {
3541  for (gr = de_ctx->flow_gh[f].src_gh[IPPROTO_TCP]->any_head; gr != NULL; gr = gr->next) {
3542  cnt_any++;
3543  }
3544  }
3545  for (f = 0; f < FLOW_STATES; f++) {
3546  for (gr = de_ctx->flow_gh[f].src_gh[IPPROTO_TCP]->ipv4_head; gr != NULL; gr = gr->next) {
3547  cnt_ipv4++;
3548  }
3549  }
3550  for (f = 0; f < FLOW_STATES; f++) {
3551  for (gr = de_ctx->flow_gh[f].src_gh[IPPROTO_TCP]->ipv6_head; gr != NULL; gr = gr->next) {
3552  cnt_ipv6++;
3553  }
3554  }
3555  if (!(de_ctx->flags & DE_QUIET)) {
3556  SCLogDebug("TCP Source address blocks: any: %4u, ipv4: %4u, ipv6: %4u.", cnt_any, cnt_ipv4, cnt_ipv6);
3557  }
3558 
3559  cnt_any = 0, cnt_ipv4 = 0, cnt_ipv6 = 0;
3560  /* UDP */
3561  for (f = 0; f < FLOW_STATES; f++) {
3562  for (gr = de_ctx->flow_gh[f].src_gh[IPPROTO_UDP]->any_head; gr != NULL; gr = gr->next) {
3563  cnt_any++;
3564  }
3565  }
3566  for (f = 0; f < FLOW_STATES; f++) {
3567  for (gr = de_ctx->flow_gh[f].src_gh[IPPROTO_UDP]->ipv4_head; gr != NULL; gr = gr->next) {
3568  cnt_ipv4++;
3569  }
3570  }
3571  for (f = 0; f < FLOW_STATES; f++) {
3572  for (gr = de_ctx->flow_gh[f].src_gh[IPPROTO_UDP]->ipv6_head; gr != NULL; gr = gr->next) {
3573  cnt_ipv6++;
3574  }
3575  }
3576  if (!(de_ctx->flags & DE_QUIET)) {
3577  SCLogDebug("UDP Source address blocks: any: %4u, ipv4: %4u, ipv6: %4u.", cnt_any, cnt_ipv4, cnt_ipv6);
3578  }
3579 
3580  cnt_any = 0, cnt_ipv4 = 0, cnt_ipv6 = 0;
3581  /* SCTP */
3582  for (f = 0; f < FLOW_STATES; f++) {
3583  for (gr = de_ctx->flow_gh[f].src_gh[IPPROTO_SCTP]->any_head; gr != NULL; gr = gr->next) {
3584  cnt_any++;
3585  }
3586  }
3587  for (f = 0; f < FLOW_STATES; f++) {
3588  for (gr = de_ctx->flow_gh[f].src_gh[IPPROTO_SCTP]->ipv4_head; gr != NULL; gr = gr->next) {
3589  cnt_ipv4++;
3590  }
3591  }
3592  for (f = 0; f < FLOW_STATES; f++) {
3593  for (gr = de_ctx->flow_gh[f].src_gh[IPPROTO_SCTP]->ipv6_head; gr != NULL; gr = gr->next) {
3594  cnt_ipv6++;
3595  }
3596  }
3597  if (!(de_ctx->flags & DE_QUIET)) {
3598  SCLogDebug("SCTP Source address blocks: any: %4u, ipv4: %4u, ipv6: %4u.", cnt_any, cnt_ipv4, cnt_ipv6);
3599  }
3600 
3601  /* ICMP */
3602  cnt_any = 0, cnt_ipv4 = 0, cnt_ipv6 = 0;
3603  for (f = 0; f < FLOW_STATES; f++) {
3604  for (gr = de_ctx->flow_gh[f].src_gh[1]->any_head; gr != NULL; gr = gr->next) {
3605  cnt_any++;
3606  }
3607  }
3608  for (f = 0; f < FLOW_STATES; f++) {
3609  for (gr = de_ctx->flow_gh[f].src_gh[1]->ipv4_head; gr != NULL; gr = gr->next) {
3610  cnt_ipv4++;
3611  }
3612  }
3613  for (f = 0; f < FLOW_STATES; f++) {
3614  for (gr = de_ctx->flow_gh[f].src_gh[1]->ipv6_head; gr != NULL; gr = gr->next) {
3615  cnt_ipv6++;
3616  }
3617  }
3618  if (!(de_ctx->flags & DE_QUIET)) {
3619  SCLogDebug("ICMP Source address blocks: any: %4u, ipv4: %4u, ipv6: %4u.", cnt_any, cnt_ipv4, cnt_ipv6);
3620  }
3621 #endif /* DEBUG */
3622  if (!(de_ctx->flags & DE_QUIET)) {
3623  SCLogInfo("building signature grouping structure, stage 2: building source address list... complete");
3624  }
3625 
3626  return 0;
3627 error:
3628  printf("SigAddressPrepareStage2 error\n");
3629  return -1;
3630 }
3631 
3632 /**
3633  * \brief Build the destination address portion of the match tree
3634  */
3635 int BuildDestinationAddressHeads(DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx, DetectAddressHead *head, int family, int flow)
3636 {
3637  Signature *tmp_s = NULL;
3638  DetectAddress *gr = NULL, *sgr = NULL, *lookup_gr = NULL;
3639  uint32_t max_idx = 0;
3640 
3641  DetectAddress *grhead = NULL, *grdsthead = NULL, *grsighead = NULL;
3642 
3643  /* based on the family, select the list we are using in the head */
3644  grhead = GetHeadPtr(head, family);
3645 
3646  /* loop through the global source address list */
3647  for (gr = grhead; gr != NULL; gr = gr->next) {
3648  //printf(" * Source group (BuildDestinationAddressHeads): "); DetectAddressPrint(gr); printf(" (%p)\n", gr);
3649 
3650  /* initialize the destination group head */
3651  gr->dst_gh = DetectAddressHeadInit();
3652  if (gr->dst_gh == NULL) {
3653  goto error;
3654  }
3655 
3656  /* use a tmp list for speeding up insertions */
3657  DetectAddress *tmp_gr_list = NULL;
3658 
3659  /* loop through all signatures in this source address group
3660  * and build the temporary destination address list for it */
3661  uint32_t sig;
3662  for (sig = 0; sig < de_ctx->sig_array_len; sig++) {
3663  if (!(gr->sh->init->sig_array[(sig/8)] & (1<<(sig%8))))
3664  continue;
3665 
3666  tmp_s = de_ctx->sig_array[sig];
3667  if (tmp_s == NULL)
3668  continue;
3669 
3670  //printf(" * (tmp) Signature %u (num %u)\n", tmp_s->id, tmp_s->num);
3671 
3672  max_idx = sig;
3673 
3674  /* build the temp list */
3675  grsighead = GetHeadPtr(&tmp_s->dst, family);
3676  for (sgr = grsighead; sgr != NULL; sgr = sgr->next) {
3677  //printf(" * (tmp) dst group: "); DetectAddressPrint(sgr); printf(" (%p)\n", sgr);
3678 
3679  if ((lookup_gr = DetectAddressLookupInList(tmp_gr_list, sgr)) == NULL) {
3680  DetectAddress *grtmp = DetectAddressCopy(sgr);
3681  if (grtmp == NULL) {
3682  goto error;
3683  }
3684  SigGroupHeadAppendSig(de_ctx,&grtmp->sh,tmp_s);
3685 
3686  DetectAddressAdd(&tmp_gr_list,grtmp);
3687  } else {
3688  /* our group will only have one sig, this one. So add that. */
3689  SigGroupHeadAppendSig(de_ctx, &lookup_gr->sh, tmp_s);
3690  lookup_gr->cnt++;
3691  }
3692  }
3693 
3694  }
3695 
3696  /* Create the destination address list, keeping in
3697  * mind the limits we use. */
3698  int groups = (flow ? de_ctx->max_uniq_toserver_dst_groups : de_ctx->max_uniq_toclient_dst_groups);
3699 
3700  CreateGroupedAddrList(de_ctx, tmp_gr_list, family, gr->dst_gh, groups,
3701  CreateGroupedAddrListCmpMpmMinlen, max_idx);
3702 
3703  /* see if the sig group head of each address group is the
3704  * same as an earlier one. If it is, free our head and use
3705  * a pointer to the earlier one. This saves _a lot_ of memory.
3706  */
3707  grdsthead = GetHeadPtr(gr->dst_gh, family);
3708  for (sgr = grdsthead; sgr != NULL; sgr = sgr->next) {
3709  //printf(" * Destination group: "); DetectAddressPrint(sgr); printf("\n");
3710 
3711  /* Because a pattern matcher context uses quite some
3712  * memory, we first check if we can reuse it from
3713  * another group head. */
3714  SigGroupHead *sgh = SigGroupHeadHashLookup(de_ctx, sgr->sh);
3715  if (sgh == NULL) {
3716  /* put the contents in our sig group head */
3717  SigGroupHeadSetSigCnt(sgr->sh, max_idx);
3718  SigGroupHeadBuildMatchArray(de_ctx, sgr->sh, max_idx);
3719 
3720  /* init the pattern matcher, this will respect the copy
3721  * setting */
3722  if (PatternMatchPrepareGroup(de_ctx, sgr->sh) < 0) {
3723  printf("PatternMatchPrepareGroup failed\n");
3724  goto error;
3725  }
3726  SigGroupHeadHashAdd(de_ctx, sgr->sh);
3727  SigGroupHeadStore(de_ctx, sgr->sh);
3728  de_ctx->gh_unique++;
3729  } else {
3730  SCLogDebug("calling SigGroupHeadFree sgr %p, sgr->sh %p", sgr, sgr->sh);
3731  SigGroupHeadFree(sgr->sh);
3732  sgr->sh = sgh;
3733 
3734  de_ctx->gh_reuse++;
3735  sgr->flags |= ADDRESS_SIGGROUPHEAD_COPY;
3736  sgr->sh->flags |= SIG_GROUP_HEAD_REFERENCED;
3737  }
3738  }
3739 
3740  /* free the temp list */
3741  DetectAddressCleanupList(tmp_gr_list);
3742  /* clear now unneeded sig group head */
3743  SCLogDebug("calling SigGroupHeadFree gr %p, gr->sh %p", gr, gr->sh);
3744  SigGroupHeadFree(gr->sh);
3745  gr->sh = NULL;
3746  }
3747 
3748  return 0;
3749 error:
3750  return -1;
3751 }
3752 
3753 //static
3754 int BuildDestinationAddressHeadsWithBothPorts(DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx, DetectAddressHead *head, int family, int flow)
3755 {
3756  Signature *tmp_s = NULL;
3757  DetectAddress *src_gr = NULL, *dst_gr = NULL, *sig_gr = NULL, *lookup_gr = NULL;
3758  DetectAddress *src_gr_head = NULL, *dst_gr_head = NULL, *sig_gr_head = NULL;
3759  uint32_t max_idx = 0;
3760 
3761  /* loop through the global source address list */
3762  src_gr_head = GetHeadPtr(head,family);
3763  for (src_gr = src_gr_head; src_gr != NULL; src_gr = src_gr->next) {
3764  //printf(" * Source group: "); DetectAddressPrint(src_gr); printf("\n");
3765 
3766  /* initialize the destination group head */
3767  src_gr->dst_gh = DetectAddressHeadInit();
3768  if (src_gr->dst_gh == NULL) {
3769  goto error;
3770  }
3771 
3772  /* use a tmp list for speeding up insertions */
3773  DetectAddress *tmp_gr_list = NULL;
3774 
3775  /* loop through all signatures in this source address group
3776  * and build the temporary destination address list for it */
3777  uint32_t sig;
3778  for (sig = 0; sig < de_ctx->sig_array_len; sig++) {
3779  if (!(src_gr->sh->init->sig_array[(sig/8)] & (1<<(sig%8))))
3780  continue;
3781 
3782  tmp_s = de_ctx->sig_array[sig];
3783  if (tmp_s == NULL)
3784  continue;
3785 
3786  //printf(" * Source group: "); DetectAddressPrint(src_gr); printf("\n");
3787 
3788  max_idx = sig;
3789 
3790  /* build the temp list */
3791  sig_gr_head = GetHeadPtr(&tmp_s->dst,family);
3792  for (sig_gr = sig_gr_head; sig_gr != NULL; sig_gr = sig_gr->next) {
3793  //printf(" * Sig dst addr: "); DetectAddressPrint(sig_gr); printf("\n");
3794 
3795  if ((lookup_gr = DetectAddressLookupInList(tmp_gr_list, sig_gr)) == NULL) {
3796  DetectAddress *grtmp = DetectAddressCopy(sig_gr);
3797  if (grtmp == NULL) {
3798  goto error;
3799  }
3800  SigGroupHeadAppendSig(de_ctx, &grtmp->sh, tmp_s);
3801 
3802  DetectAddressAdd(&tmp_gr_list,grtmp);
3803  } else {
3804  /* our group will only have one sig, this one. So add that. */
3805  SigGroupHeadAppendSig(de_ctx, &lookup_gr->sh, tmp_s);
3806  lookup_gr->cnt++;
3807  }
3808 
3809  SCLogDebug("calling SigGroupHeadFree sig_gr %p, sig_gr->sh %p", sig_gr, sig_gr->sh);
3810  SigGroupHeadFree(sig_gr->sh);
3811  sig_gr->sh = NULL;
3812  }
3813  }
3814 
3815  /* Create the destination address list, keeping in
3816  * mind the limits we use. */
3817  int groups = (flow ? de_ctx->max_uniq_toserver_dst_groups : de_ctx->max_uniq_toclient_dst_groups);
3818 
3819  CreateGroupedAddrList(de_ctx, tmp_gr_list, family, src_gr->dst_gh, groups,
3820  CreateGroupedAddrListCmpMpmMinlen, max_idx);
3821 
3822  /* add the ports to the dst address groups and the sigs
3823  * to the ports */
3824  dst_gr_head = GetHeadPtr(src_gr->dst_gh,family);
3825  for (dst_gr = dst_gr_head; dst_gr != NULL; dst_gr = dst_gr->next) {
3826  //printf(" * Destination group: "); DetectAddressPrint(dst_gr); printf("\n");
3827 
3828  dst_gr->flags |= ADDRESS_HAVEPORT;
3829 
3830  if (dst_gr->sh == NULL)
3831  continue;
3832 
3833  /* we will reuse address sig group heads at this points,
3834  * because if the sigs are the same, the ports will be
3835  * the same. Saves memory and a lot of init time. */
3836  SigGroupHead *lookup_sgh = SigGroupHeadHashLookup(de_ctx, dst_gr->sh);
3837  if (lookup_sgh == NULL) {
3838  DetectPortSpHashReset(de_ctx);
3839 
3840  uint32_t sig2;
3841  for (sig2 = 0; sig2 < max_idx+1; sig2++) {
3842  if (!(dst_gr->sh->init->sig_array[(sig2/8)] & (1<<(sig2%8))))
3843  continue;
3844 
3845  Signature *s = de_ctx->sig_array[sig2];
3846  if (s == NULL)
3847  continue;
3848 
3849  //printf(" + Destination group (grouped): "); DetectAddressPrint(dst_gr); printf("\n");
3850 
3851  DetectPort *sdp = s->sp;
3852  for ( ; sdp != NULL; sdp = sdp->next) {
3853  DetectPort *lookup_port = DetectPortSpHashLookup(de_ctx, sdp);
3854  if (lookup_port == NULL) {
3855  DetectPort *port = DetectPortCopySingle(de_ctx,sdp);
3856  if (port == NULL)
3857  goto error;
3858 
3859  SigGroupHeadAppendSig(de_ctx, &port->sh, s);
3860  DetectPortSpHashAdd(de_ctx, port);
3861  port->cnt = 1;
3862  } else {
3863  SigGroupHeadAppendSig(de_ctx, &lookup_port->sh, s);
3864  lookup_port->cnt++;
3865  }
3866  }
3867  }
3868 
3869  int spgroups = (flow ? de_ctx->max_uniq_toserver_sp_groups : de_ctx->max_uniq_toclient_sp_groups);
3870 
3871  CreateGroupedPortList(de_ctx, de_ctx->sport_hash_table, &dst_gr->port, spgroups,
3872  CreateGroupedPortListCmpMpmMinlen, max_idx);
3873 
3874  SCLogDebug("adding sgh %p to the hash", dst_gr->sh);
3875  SigGroupHeadHashAdd(de_ctx, dst_gr->sh);
3876 
3877  dst_gr->sh->init->port = dst_gr->port;
3878  /* mark this head for deletion once we no longer need
3879  * the hash. We're only using the port ptr, so no problem
3880  * when we remove this after initialization is done */
3881  dst_gr->sh->flags |= SIG_GROUP_HEAD_FREE;
3882 
3883  /* for each destination port we setup the siggrouphead here */
3884  DetectPort *sp = dst_gr->port;
3885  for ( ; sp != NULL; sp = sp->next) {
3886  //printf(" * Src Port(range): "); DetectPortPrint(sp); printf("\n");
3887 
3888  if (sp->sh == NULL)
3889  continue;
3890 
3891  /* we will reuse address sig group heads at this points,
3892  * because if the sigs are the same, the ports will be
3893  * the same. Saves memory and a lot of init time. */
3894  SigGroupHead *lookup_sp_sgh = SigGroupHeadSPortHashLookup(de_ctx, sp->sh);
3895  if (lookup_sp_sgh == NULL) {
3896  DetectPortDpHashReset(de_ctx);
3897  uint32_t sig2;
3898  for (sig2 = 0; sig2 < max_idx+1; sig2++) {
3899  if (!(sp->sh->init->sig_array[(sig2/8)] & (1<<(sig2%8))))
3900  continue;
3901 
3902  Signature *s = de_ctx->sig_array[sig2];
3903  if (s == NULL)
3904  continue;
3905 
3906  DetectPort *sdp = s->dp;
3907  for ( ; sdp != NULL; sdp = sdp->next) {
3908  DetectPort *lookup_port = DetectPortDpHashLookup(de_ctx,sdp);
3909  if (lookup_port == NULL) {
3910  DetectPort *port = DetectPortCopySingle(de_ctx,sdp);
3911  if (port == NULL)
3912  goto error;
3913 
3914  SigGroupHeadAppendSig(de_ctx, &port->sh, s);
3915  DetectPortDpHashAdd(de_ctx,port);
3916  port->cnt = 1;
3917  } else {
3918  SigGroupHeadAppendSig(de_ctx, &lookup_port->sh, s);
3919  lookup_port->cnt++;
3920  }
3921  }
3922  }
3923 
3924  int dpgroups = (flow ? de_ctx->max_uniq_toserver_dp_groups : de_ctx->max_uniq_toclient_dp_groups);
3925 
3926  CreateGroupedPortList(de_ctx, de_ctx->dport_hash_table,
3927  &sp->dst_ph, dpgroups,
3928  CreateGroupedPortListCmpMpmMinlen, max_idx);
3929 
3930  SigGroupHeadSPortHashAdd(de_ctx, sp->sh);
3931 
3932  sp->sh->init->port = sp->dst_ph;
3933  /* mark this head for deletion once we no longer need
3934  * the hash. We're only using the port ptr, so no problem
3935  * when we remove this after initialization is done */
3936  sp->sh->flags |= SIG_GROUP_HEAD_FREE;
3937 
3938  /* for each destination port we setup the siggrouphead here */
3939  DetectPort *dp = sp->dst_ph;
3940  for ( ; dp != NULL; dp = dp->next) {
3941  if (dp->sh == NULL)
3942  continue;
3943 
3944  /* Because a pattern matcher context uses quite some
3945  * memory, we first check if we can reuse it from
3946  * another group head. */
3947  SigGroupHead *lookup_dp_sgh = SigGroupHeadDPortHashLookup(de_ctx, dp->sh);
3948  if (lookup_dp_sgh == NULL) {
3949  SCLogDebug("dp %p dp->sh %p is the original (sp %p, dst_gr %p, src_gr %p)", dp, dp->sh, sp, dst_gr, src_gr);
3950 
3951  SigGroupHeadSetSigCnt(dp->sh, max_idx);
3952  SigGroupHeadBuildMatchArray(de_ctx,dp->sh, max_idx);
3953 
3954  /* init the pattern matcher, this will respect the copy
3955  * setting */
3956  if (PatternMatchPrepareGroup(de_ctx, dp->sh) < 0) {
3957  printf("PatternMatchPrepareGroup failed\n");
3958  goto error;
3959  }
3960  SigGroupHeadDPortHashAdd(de_ctx, dp->sh);
3961  SigGroupHeadStore(de_ctx, dp->sh);
3962  de_ctx->gh_unique++;
3963  } else {
3964  SCLogDebug("dp %p dp->sh %p is a copy", dp, dp->sh);
3965 
3966  SigGroupHeadFree(dp->sh);
3967  dp->sh = lookup_dp_sgh;
3968  dp->flags |= PORT_SIGGROUPHEAD_COPY;
3969  dp->sh->flags |= SIG_GROUP_HEAD_REFERENCED;
3970 
3971  de_ctx->gh_reuse++;
3972  }
3973  }
3974  /* sig group head found in hash, free it and use the hashed one */
3975  } else {
3976  SigGroupHeadFree(sp->sh);
3977  sp->sh = lookup_sp_sgh;
3978  sp->flags |= PORT_SIGGROUPHEAD_COPY;
3979  sp->sh->flags |= SIG_GROUP_HEAD_REFERENCED;
3980 
3981  SCLogDebug("replacing sp->dst_ph %p with lookup_sp_sgh->init->port %p", sp->dst_ph, lookup_sp_sgh->init->port);
3982  DetectPortCleanupList(sp->dst_ph);
3983  sp->dst_ph = lookup_sp_sgh->init->port;
3984  sp->flags |= PORT_GROUP_PORTS_COPY;
3985 
3986  de_ctx->gh_reuse++;
3987  }
3988  }
3989  } else {
3990  SigGroupHeadFree(dst_gr->sh);
3991  dst_gr->sh = lookup_sgh;
3992  dst_gr->flags |= ADDRESS_SIGGROUPHEAD_COPY;
3993  dst_gr->sh->flags |= SIG_GROUP_HEAD_REFERENCED;
3994 
3995  SCLogDebug("replacing dst_gr->port %p with lookup_sgh->init->port %p", dst_gr->port, lookup_sgh->init->port);
3996  DetectPortCleanupList(dst_gr->port);
3997  dst_gr->port = lookup_sgh->init->port;
3998  dst_gr->flags |= ADDRESS_PORTS_COPY;
3999 
4000  de_ctx->gh_reuse++;
4001  }
4002  }
4003  /* free the temp list */
4004  DetectAddressCleanupList(tmp_gr_list);
4005  /* clear now unneeded sig group head */
4006  SigGroupHeadFree(src_gr->sh);
4007  src_gr->sh = NULL;
4008 
4009  /* free dst addr sgh's */
4010  dst_gr_head = GetHeadPtr(src_gr->dst_gh,family);
4011  for (dst_gr = dst_gr_head; dst_gr != NULL; dst_gr = dst_gr->next) {
4012  if (!(dst_gr->flags & ADDRESS_SIGGROUPHEAD_COPY)) {
4013  if (!(dst_gr->sh->flags & SIG_GROUP_HEAD_REFERENCED)) {
4014  SCLogDebug("removing sgh %p from hash", dst_gr->sh);
4015 
4016  int r = SigGroupHeadHashRemove(de_ctx,dst_gr->sh);
4017  BUG_ON(r == -1);
4018  if (r == 0) {
4019  SCLogDebug("removed sgh %p from hash", dst_gr->sh);
4020  SigGroupHeadFree(dst_gr->sh);
4021  dst_gr->sh = NULL;
4022  }
4023  }
4024  }
4025  }
4026  }
4027 
4028  return 0;
4029 error:
4030  return -1;
4031 }

4033 static void DetectEngineBuildDecoderEventSgh(DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx)
4034 {
4035  if (de_ctx->decoder_event_sgh == NULL)
4036  return;
4037 
4038  uint32_t max_idx = DetectEngineGetMaxSigId(de_ctx);
4039  SigGroupHeadSetSigCnt(de_ctx->decoder_event_sgh, max_idx);
4040  SigGroupHeadBuildMatchArray(de_ctx, de_ctx->decoder_event_sgh, max_idx);
4041 }

4043 int SigAddressPrepareStage3(DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx)
4044 {
4045  int r;
4046 
4047  if (!(de_ctx->flags & DE_QUIET)) {
4048  SCLogDebug("building signature grouping structure, stage 3: "
4049  "building destination address lists...");
4050  }
4051  //DetectAddressPrintMemory();
4052  //DetectSigGroupPrintMemory();
4053  //DetectPortPrintMemory();
4054 
4055  int f = 0;
4056  int proto;
4057  for (f = 0; f < FLOW_STATES; f++) {
4058  r = BuildDestinationAddressHeadsWithBothPorts(de_ctx, de_ctx->flow_gh[f].src_gh[IPPROTO_TCP],AF_INET,f);
4059  if (r < 0) {
4060  printf ("BuildDestinationAddressHeads(src_gh[6],AF_INET) failed\n");
4061  goto error;
4062  }
4063  r = BuildDestinationAddressHeadsWithBothPorts(de_ctx, de_ctx->flow_gh[f].src_gh[IPPROTO_UDP],AF_INET,f);
4064  if (r < 0) {
4065  printf ("BuildDestinationAddressHeads(src_gh[17],AF_INET) failed\n");
4066  goto error;
4067  }
4068  r = BuildDestinationAddressHeadsWithBothPorts(de_ctx, de_ctx->flow_gh[f].src_gh[IPPROTO_SCTP],AF_INET,f);
4069  if (r < 0) {
4070  printf ("BuildDestinationAddressHeads(src_gh[IPPROTO_SCTP],AF_INET) failed\n");
4071  goto error;
4072  }
4073  r = BuildDestinationAddressHeadsWithBothPorts(de_ctx, de_ctx->flow_gh[f].src_gh[IPPROTO_TCP],AF_INET6,f);
4074  if (r < 0) {
4075  printf ("BuildDestinationAddressHeads(src_gh[6],AF_INET) failed\n");
4076  goto error;
4077  }
4078  r = BuildDestinationAddressHeadsWithBothPorts(de_ctx, de_ctx->flow_gh[f].src_gh[IPPROTO_UDP],AF_INET6,f);
4079  if (r < 0) {
4080  printf ("BuildDestinationAddressHeads(src_gh[17],AF_INET) failed\n");
4081  goto error;
4082  }
4083  r = BuildDestinationAddressHeadsWithBothPorts(de_ctx, de_ctx->flow_gh[f].src_gh[IPPROTO_SCTP],AF_INET6,f);
4084  if (r < 0) {
4085  printf ("BuildDestinationAddressHeads(src_gh[IPPROTO_SCTP],AF_INET) failed\n");
4086  goto error;
4087  }
4088  r = BuildDestinationAddressHeadsWithBothPorts(de_ctx, de_ctx->flow_gh[f].src_gh[IPPROTO_TCP],AF_UNSPEC,f);
4089  if (r < 0) {
4090  printf ("BuildDestinationAddressHeads(src_gh[6],AF_INET) failed\n");
4091  goto error;
4092  }
4093  r = BuildDestinationAddressHeadsWithBothPorts(de_ctx, de_ctx->flow_gh[f].src_gh[IPPROTO_UDP],AF_UNSPEC,f);
4094  if (r < 0) {
4095  printf ("BuildDestinationAddressHeads(src_gh[17],AF_INET) failed\n");
4096  goto error;
4097  }
4098  r = BuildDestinationAddressHeadsWithBothPorts(de_ctx, de_ctx->flow_gh[f].src_gh[IPPROTO_SCTP],AF_UNSPEC,f);
4099  if (r < 0) {
4100  printf ("BuildDestinationAddressHeads(src_gh[IPPROTO_SCTP],AF_INET) failed\n");
4101  goto error;
4102  }
4103  for (proto = 0; proto < 256; proto++) {
4104  if (proto == IPPROTO_TCP || proto == IPPROTO_UDP || proto == IPPROTO_SCTP)
4105  continue;
4106 
4107  r = BuildDestinationAddressHeads(de_ctx, de_ctx->flow_gh[f].src_gh[proto],AF_INET,f);
4108  if (r < 0) {
4109  printf ("BuildDestinationAddressHeads(src_gh[%" PRId32 "],AF_INET) failed\n", proto);
4110  goto error;
4111  }
4112  r = BuildDestinationAddressHeads(de_ctx, de_ctx->flow_gh[f].src_gh[proto],AF_INET6,f);
4113  if (r < 0) {
4114  printf ("BuildDestinationAddressHeads(src_gh[%" PRId32 "],AF_INET6) failed\n", proto);
4115  goto error;
4116  }
4117  r = BuildDestinationAddressHeads(de_ctx, de_ctx->flow_gh[f].src_gh[proto],AF_UNSPEC,f); /* for any */
4118  if (r < 0) {
4119  printf ("BuildDestinationAddressHeads(src_gh[%" PRId32 "],AF_UNSPEC) failed\n", proto);
4120  goto error;
4121  }
4122  }
4123  }
4124 
4125  /* prepare the decoder event sgh */
4126  DetectEngineBuildDecoderEventSgh(de_ctx);
4127 
4128  /* cleanup group head (uri)content_array's */
4129  SigGroupHeadFreeMpmArrays(de_ctx);
4130  /* cleanup group head sig arrays */
4131  SigGroupHeadFreeSigArrays(de_ctx);
4132 
4133  /* cleanup the hashes now since we won't need them
4134  * after the initialization phase. */
4135  SigGroupHeadHashFree(de_ctx);
4136  SigGroupHeadDPortHashFree(de_ctx);
4137  SigGroupHeadSPortHashFree(de_ctx);
4138  SigGroupHeadMpmHashFree(de_ctx);
4139  SigGroupHeadMpmUriHashFree(de_ctx);
4140  DetectPortDpHashFree(de_ctx);
4141  DetectPortSpHashFree(de_ctx);
4142 
4143  if (!(de_ctx->flags & DE_QUIET)) {
4144  SCLogDebug("max sig id %" PRIu32 ", array size %" PRIu32 "", DetectEngineGetMaxSigId(de_ctx), DetectEngineGetMaxSigId(de_ctx) / 8 + 1);
4145  SCLogDebug("signature group heads: unique %" PRIu32 ", copies %" PRIu32 ".", de_ctx->gh_unique, de_ctx->gh_reuse);
4146  SCLogDebug("port maxgroups: %" PRIu32 ", avg %" PRIu32 ", tot %" PRIu32 "", g_groupportlist_maxgroups, g_groupportlist_groupscnt ? g_groupportlist_totgroups/g_groupportlist_groupscnt : 0, g_groupportlist_totgroups);
4147 
4148  SCLogInfo("building signature grouping structure, stage 3: building destination address lists... complete");
4149  }
4150  return 0;
4151 error:
4152  printf("SigAddressPrepareStage3 error\n");
4153  return -1;
4154 }

4156 int SigAddressCleanupStage1(DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx)
4157 {
4158  BUG_ON(de_ctx == NULL);
4159 
4160  if (!(de_ctx->flags & DE_QUIET)) {
4161  SCLogDebug("cleaning up signature grouping structure...");
4162  }
4163 
4164  int f, proto;
4165  for (f = 0; f < FLOW_STATES; f++) {
4166  for (proto = 0; proto < 256; proto++) {
4167  /* XXX fix this */
4168  DetectAddressHeadFree(de_ctx->flow_gh[f].src_gh[proto]);
4169  de_ctx->flow_gh[f].src_gh[proto] = NULL;
4170  }
4171  }
4172 
4173  if (de_ctx->decoder_event_sgh)
4174  SigGroupHeadFree(de_ctx->decoder_event_sgh);
4175  de_ctx->decoder_event_sgh = NULL;
4176 
4177  IPOnlyDeinit(de_ctx, &de_ctx->io_ctx);
4178 
4179  if (!(de_ctx->flags & DE_QUIET)) {
4180  SCLogInfo("cleaning up signature grouping structure... complete");
4181  }
4182  return 0;
4183 }

4215 void DbgSghContainsSig(DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx, SigGroupHead *sgh, uint32_t sid)

4218  printf("\n");

4224  if (!(sgh->init->sig_array[(sig/8)] & (1<<(sig%8))))
4225  continue;

4228  if (s == NULL)
4229  continue;
4230

4233  }
4234  }
4235  printf("\n");

4240 {

4260  SCLogDebug("http_uri content min mpm len: %u", sgh->mpm_uricontent_minlen);
4261  }
4262 
4263  if (de_ctx->decoder_event_sgh != NULL) {
4264  /* no need to set filestore count here as that would make a
4265  * signature not decode event only. */
4266  }
4267 
4268  SCFree(de_ctx->sgh_array);
4269  de_ctx->sgh_array_cnt = 0;
4270  de_ctx->sgh_array_size = 0;
4271 
4272  SCReturnInt(0);
4273 }

4587 static int SigMatchListLen(SigMatch *sm)
4588 {
4589  int len = 0;
4590  for (; sm != NULL; sm = sm->next)
4591  len++;
4592 
4593  return len;
4594 }

4596 static int SigMatchPrepare(DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx)
4597 {
4598  SCEnter();
4599 
4600  Signature *s = de_ctx->sig_list;
4601  for (; s != NULL; s = s->next) {
4602  int type;
4603  for (type = 0; type < DETECT_SM_LIST_MAX; type++) {
4604  SigMatch *sm = s->sm_lists[type];
4605  int len = SigMatchListLen(sm);
4606  if (len == 0)
4607  s->sm_arrays[type] = NULL;
4608  else {
4609  SigMatchData *smd = (SigMatchData*)SCMalloc(len * sizeof(SigMatchData));
4610  if (smd == NULL) {
4611  SCLogError(SC_ERR_DETECT_PREPARE, "initializing the detection engine failed");
4612  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
4613  }
4614  /* Copy sm type and Context into array */
4615  s->sm_arrays[type] = smd;
4616  for (; sm != NULL; sm = sm->next, smd++) {
4617  smd->type = sm->type;
4618  smd->ctx = sm->ctx;
4619  smd->is_last = (sm->next == NULL);
4620  }
4621  }
4622  }
4623  }
4624 
4625  SCReturnInt(0);
4626 }

4628 /**
4629  * \brief Convert the signature list into the runtime match structure.
4630  *
4631  * \param de_ctx Pointer to the Detection Engine Context whose Signatures have
4632  * to be processed
4633  *
4634  * \retval 0 On Success.
4635  * \retval -1 On failure.
4636  */
4637 int SigGroupBuild(DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx)
4638 {

4640 
4641  /* Assign the unique order id of signatures after sorting,
4642  * so the IP Only engine process them in order too. Also
4643  * reset the old signums and assign new signums. We would
4644  * have experienced Sig reordering by now, hence the new
4645  * signums. */

4647  while (s != NULL) {

4649 
4650  s = s->next;
4651  }
4652 
4653  if (DetectSetFastPatternAndItsId(de_ctx) < 0)
4654  return -1;
4655 
4656  /* if we are using single sgh_mpm_context then let us init the standard mpm
4657  * contexts using the mpm_ctx factory */
4658  if (de_ctx->sgh_mpm_context == ENGINE_SGH_MPM_FACTORY_CONTEXT_SINGLE) {
4659  SigInitStandardMpmFactoryContexts(de_ctx);
4660  }
4661

4664  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);

4925 static inline void PrintFeatureList(int flags, char sep)
4926 {
4927  int prev = 0;
4928  if (flags & SIGMATCH_NOOPT) {
4929  printf("No option");
4930  prev = 1;
4931  }
4932  if (flags & SIGMATCH_IPONLY_COMPAT) {
4933  if (prev == 1)
4934  printf("%c", sep);
4935  printf("compatible with IP only rule");
4936  prev = 1;
4937  }
4938  if (flags & SIGMATCH_DEONLY_COMPAT) {
4939  if (prev == 1)
4940  printf("%c", sep);
4941  printf("compatible with decoder event only rule");
4942  prev = 1;
4943  }
4944  if (flags & SIGMATCH_PAYLOAD) {
4945  if (prev == 1)
4946  printf("%c", sep);
4947  printf("payload inspecting keyword");
4948  prev = 1;
4949  }
4950  if (prev == 0) {
4951  printf("none");
4952  }
4953 }
4954 
4955 static inline void SigMultilinePrint(int i, char *prefix)
4956 {
4957  if (sigmatch_table[i].desc) {
4958  printf("%sDescription: %s\n", prefix, sigmatch_table[i].desc);
4959  }
4960  printf("%sProtocol: %s\n", prefix,
4961  AppLayerGetProtoName(sigmatch_table[i].alproto));
4962  printf("%sFeatures: ", prefix);
4963  PrintFeatureList(sigmatch_table[i].flags, ',');
4964  if (sigmatch_table[i].url) {
4965  printf("\n%sDocumentation: %s", prefix, sigmatch_table[i].url);
4966  }
4967  printf("\n");
4968 }
4969 
4970 void SigTableList(const char *keyword)
4971 {
4972  size_t size = sizeof(sigmatch_table) / sizeof(SigTableElmt);
4973  size_t i;
4974  char *proto_name;
4975 
4976  if (keyword == NULL) {
4977  printf("=====Supported keywords=====\n");
4978  for (i = 0; i < size; i++) {
4979  if (sigmatch_table[i].name != NULL) {
4980  if (sigmatch_table[i].flags & SIGMATCH_NOT_BUILT) {
4981  printf("- %s (not built-in)\n", sigmatch_table[i].name);
4982  } else {
4983  printf("- %s\n", sigmatch_table[i].name);
4984  }
4985  }
4986  }
4987  } else if (!strcmp("csv", keyword)) {
4988  printf("name;description;app layer;features;documentation\n");
4989  for (i = 0; i < size; i++) {
4990  if (sigmatch_table[i].name != NULL) {
4991  if (sigmatch_table[i].flags & SIGMATCH_NOT_BUILT) {
4992  continue;
4993  }
4994  printf("%s;", sigmatch_table[i].name);
4995  if (sigmatch_table[i].desc) {
4996  printf("%s", sigmatch_table[i].desc);
4997  }
4998  /* Build feature */
4999  proto_name = AppLayerGetProtoName(sigmatch_table[i].alproto);
5000  printf(";%s;", proto_name ? proto_name : "Unset");
5001  PrintFeatureList(sigmatch_table[i].flags, ':');
5002  printf(";");
5003  if (sigmatch_table[i].url) {
5004  printf("%s", sigmatch_table[i].url);
5005  }
5006  printf(";");
5007  printf("\n");
5008  }
5009  }
5010  } else if (!strcmp("all", keyword)) {
5011  for (i = 0; i < size; i++) {
5012  printf("%s:\n", sigmatch_table[i].name);
5013  SigMultilinePrint(i, "\t");
5014  }
5015  } else {
5016  for (i = 0; i < size; i++) {
5017  if ((sigmatch_table[i].name != NULL) &&
5018  !strcmp(sigmatch_table[i].name, keyword)) {
5019  printf("= %s =\n", sigmatch_table[i].name);
5020  if (sigmatch_table[i].flags & SIGMATCH_NOT_BUILT) {
5021  printf("Not built-in\n");
5022  return;
5023  }
5024  SigMultilinePrint(i, "");
5025  return;
5026  }
5027  }
5028  }
5029  return;
5030 }

5509 static int SigTest06Real (int mpm_type)
5510 {
5511  uint8_t *buf = (uint8_t *)
5512  "GET /one/ HTTP/1.1\r\n" /* 20 */
5513  "Host: one.example.org\r\n" /* 23, 43 */
5514  "\r\n\r\n" /* 4, 47 */
5515  "GET /two/ HTTP/1.1\r\n" /* 20, 67 */
5516  "Host: two.example.org\r\n" /* 23, 90 */
5517  "\r\n\r\n"; /* 4, 94 */
5518  uint16_t buflen = strlen((char *)buf);
5519  Packet *p = NULL;
5520  ThreadVars th_v;
5521  DetectEngineThreadCtx *det_ctx = NULL;
5522  Flow f;
5523  TcpSession ssn;
5524  int result = 0;
5525  AppLayerParserThreadCtx *alp_tctx = AppLayerParserThreadCtxAlloc();
5526 
5527  memset(&th_v, 0, sizeof(th_v));
5528  memset(&f, 0, sizeof(f));
5529  memset(&ssn, 0, sizeof(ssn));
5530 
5531  p = UTHBuildPacket((uint8_t *)buf, buflen, IPPROTO_TCP);
5532 
5533  FLOW_INITIALIZE(&f);
5534  f.protoctx = (void *)&ssn;
5535  f.flags |= FLOW_IPV4;
5536  f.proto = IPPROTO_TCP;
5537  p->flow = &f;
5538  p->flowflags |= FLOW_PKT_TOSERVER;
5539  p->flowflags |= FLOW_PKT_ESTABLISHED;
5540  p->flags |= PKT_HAS_FLOW|PKT_STREAM_EST;
5541  f.alproto = ALPROTO_HTTP;
5542 
5543  StreamTcpInitConfig(TRUE);
5544 
5545  DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx = DetectEngineCtxInit();
5546  if (de_ctx == NULL) {
5547  goto end;
5548  }
5549 
5550  de_ctx->mpm_matcher = mpm_type;
5551  de_ctx->flags |= DE_QUIET;
5552 
5553  de_ctx->sig_list = SigInit(de_ctx,"alert tcp any any -> any any (msg:\"HTTP URI cap\"; content:\"GET \"; depth:4; pcre:\"/GET (?P<pkt_http_uri>.*) HTTP\\/\\d\\.\\d\\r\\n/G\"; sid:1;)");
5554  if (de_ctx->sig_list == NULL) {
5555  result = 0;
5556  goto end;
5557  }
5558 
5559  de_ctx->sig_list->next = SigInit(de_ctx,"alert tcp any any -> any any (msg:\"HTTP URI test\"; uricontent:\"two\"; sid:2;)");
5560  if (de_ctx->sig_list->next == NULL) {
5561  result = 0;
5562  goto end;
5563  }
5564 
5565  SigGroupBuild(de_ctx);
5566  DetectEngineThreadCtxInit(&th_v, (void *)de_ctx, (void *)&det_ctx);
5567 
5568  SCMutexLock(&f.m);
5569  int r = AppLayerParserParse(alp_tctx, &f, ALPROTO_HTTP, STREAM_TOSERVER, buf, buflen);
5570  if (r != 0) {
5571  printf("toserver chunk 1 returned %" PRId32 ", expected 0: ", r);
5572  result = 0;
5573  SCMutexUnlock(&f.m);
5574  goto end;
5575  }
5576  SCMutexUnlock(&f.m);
5577 
5578  SigMatchSignatures(&th_v, de_ctx, det_ctx, p);

6432 static int SigTest17Real (int mpm_type)
6433 {
6434  uint8_t *buf = (uint8_t *)
6435  "GET /one/ HTTP/1.1\r\n" /* 20 */
6436  "Host: one.example.org\r\n" /* 23, 43 */
6437  "\r\n\r\n" /* 4, 47 */
6438  "GET /two/ HTTP/1.1\r\n" /* 20, 67 */
6439  "Host: two.example.org\r\n" /* 23, 90 */
6440  "\r\n\r\n"; /* 4, 94 */
6441  uint16_t buflen = strlen((char *)buf);
6442  Packet *p = NULL;
6443  ThreadVars th_v;
6444  DetectEngineThreadCtx *det_ctx = NULL;
6445  int result = 0;
6446 
6447  memset(&th_v, 0, sizeof(th_v));
6448 
6449  p = UTHBuildPacketSrcDstPorts((uint8_t *)buf, buflen, IPPROTO_TCP, 12345, 80);
6450 
6451  ConfCreateContextBackup();
6452  ConfInit();
6453  ConfYamlLoadString(dummy_conf_string, strlen(dummy_conf_string));
6454 
6455  DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx = DetectEngineCtxInit();
6456  if (de_ctx == NULL) {
6457  goto end;
6458  }
6459 
6460  de_ctx->mpm_matcher = mpm_type;
6461  de_ctx->flags |= DE_QUIET;
6462 
6463  de_ctx->sig_list = SigInit(de_ctx,"alert tcp any any -> any $HTTP_PORTS (msg:\"HTTP host cap\"; content:\"Host:\"; pcre:\"/^Host: (?P<pkt_http_host>.*)\\r\\n/m\"; noalert; sid:1;)");
6464  if (de_ctx->sig_list == NULL) {
6465  result = 0;
6466  goto end;
6467  }
6468 
6469  SigGroupBuild(de_ctx);
6470  DetectEngineThreadCtxInit(&th_v, (void *)de_ctx,(void *)&det_ctx);
6471 
6472  SigMatchSignatures(&th_v, de_ctx, det_ctx, p);
6473  PktVar *pv_hn = PktVarGet(p, "http_host");
6474  if (pv_hn != NULL) {
6475  if (memcmp(pv_hn->value, "one.example.org", pv_hn->value_len < 15 ? pv_hn->value_len : 15) == 0)
6476  result = 1;
6477  else {
6478  printf("\"");
6479  PrintRawUriFp(stdout, pv_hn->value, pv_hn->value_len);
6480  printf("\" != \"one.example.org\": ");
6481  }
6482  PktVarFree(pv_hn);
6483  } else {
6484  printf("Pkt var http_host not captured: ");
6485  }
6486 
6487 end:
6488  if (de_ctx != NULL) {
6489  SigGroupCleanup(de_ctx);
6490  SigCleanSignatures(de_ctx);
6491  if (det_ctx != NULL)
6492  DetectEngineThreadCtxDeinit(&th_v, (void *)det_ctx);
6493  DetectEngineCtxFree(de_ctx);
6494  }
6495  ConfDeInit();
6496  ConfRestoreContextBackup();
6497  UTHFreePackets(&p, 1);
6498  return result;
6499 }

7003 int SigTest24IPV4Keyword(void)
7004 {
7005  uint8_t valid_raw_ipv4[] = {
7006  0x45, 0x00, 0x00, 0x54, 0x00, 0x00, 0x40, 0x00,
7007  0x40, 0x01, 0xb7, 0x52, 0xc0, 0xa8, 0x01, 0x03,
7008  0xc0, 0xa8, 0x01, 0x03};
7009 
7010  uint8_t invalid_raw_ipv4[] = {
7011  0x45, 0x00, 0x00, 0x54, 0x00, 0x00, 0x40, 0x00,
7012  0x40, 0x01, 0xb7, 0x52, 0xc0, 0xa8, 0x01, 0x03,
7013  0xc0, 0xa8, 0x01, 0x06};
7014 
7015  Packet *p1 = SCMalloc(SIZE_OF_PACKET);
7016  if (unlikely(p1 == NULL))
7017  return 0;
7018  Packet *p2 = SCMalloc(SIZE_OF_PACKET);
7019  if (unlikely(p2 == NULL)) {
7020  SCFree(p1);
7021  return 0;
7022  }
7023  ThreadVars th_v;
7024  DetectEngineThreadCtx *det_ctx = NULL;
7025  int result = 0;
7026 
7027  uint8_t *buf = (uint8_t *)"GET /one/ HTTP/1.0\r\n"
7028  "\r\n\r\n";
7029  uint16_t buflen = strlen((char *)buf);
7030 
7031  memset(&th_v, 0, sizeof(ThreadVars));
7032  memset(p1, 0, SIZE_OF_PACKET);
7033  memset(p2, 0, SIZE_OF_PACKET);
7034  PACKET_RESET_CHECKSUMS(p1);
7035  PACKET_RESET_CHECKSUMS(p2);
7036 
7037  p1->ip4h = (IPV4Hdr *)valid_raw_ipv4;
7038 
7039  p1->src.family = AF_INET;
7040  p1->dst.family = AF_INET;
7041  p1->payload = buf;
7042  p1->payload_len = buflen;
7043  p1->proto = IPPROTO_TCP;
7044 
7045  p2->ip4h = (IPV4Hdr *)invalid_raw_ipv4;
7046 
7047  p2->src.family = AF_INET;
7048  p2->dst.family = AF_INET;
7049  p2->payload = buf;
7050  p2->payload_len = buflen;
7051  p2->proto = IPPROTO_TCP;
7052 
7053  DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx = DetectEngineCtxInit();
7054  if (de_ctx == NULL) {
7055  goto end;
7056  }
7057 
7058  de_ctx->flags |= DE_QUIET;
7059 
7060  de_ctx->sig_list = SigInit(de_ctx,
7061  "alert ip any any -> any any "
7062  "(content:\"/one/\"; ipv4-csum:valid; "
7063  "msg:\"ipv4-csum keyword check(1)\"; sid:1;)");
7064  if (de_ctx->sig_list == NULL) {
7065  printf("sig 1 parse: ");
7066  goto end;
7067  }
7068 
7069  de_ctx->sig_list->next = SigInit(de_ctx,
7070  "alert ip any any -> any any "
7071  "(content:\"/one/\"; ipv4-csum:invalid; "
7072  "msg:\"ipv4-csum keyword check(1)\"; "
7073  "sid:2;)");
7074  if (de_ctx->sig_list->next == NULL) {
7075  printf("sig 2 parse: ");
7076  goto end;
7077  }
7078 
7079  SigGroupBuild(de_ctx);
7080  DetectEngineThreadCtxInit(&th_v, (void *)de_ctx,(void *)&det_ctx);
7081 
7082  SigMatchSignatures(&th_v, de_ctx, det_ctx, p1);
7083  if (!(PacketAlertCheck(p1, 1))) {
7084  printf("signature 1 didn't match, but should have: ");
7085  goto end;
7086  }
7087 
7088  SigMatchSignatures(&th_v, de_ctx, det_ctx, p2);
7089  if (!((PacketAlertCheck(p2, 2)))) {
7090  printf("signature 2 didn't match, but should have: ");
7091  goto end;
7092  }
7093 
7094  result = 1;
7095 end:
7096  if (det_ctx != NULL) {
7097  SigGroupCleanup(de_ctx);
7098  SigCleanSignatures(de_ctx);
7099  DetectEngineThreadCtxDeinit(&th_v, (void *)det_ctx);
7100  DetectEngineCtxFree(de_ctx);
7101  }
7102  SCFree(p1);
7103  SCFree(p2);
7104  return result;

8903 int SigTest38Real(int mpm_type)
8904 {
8905  Packet *p1 = SCMalloc(SIZE_OF_PACKET);
8906  if (unlikely(p1 == NULL))
8907  return 0;
8908  ThreadVars th_v;
8909  DetectEngineThreadCtx *det_ctx = NULL;
8910  int result = 1;
8911  uint8_t raw_eth[] = {
8912  0x00, 0x00, 0x03, 0x04, 0x00, 0x06, 0x00,
8913  0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00,
8914  0x08, 0x00
8915  };
8916  uint8_t raw_ipv4[] = {
8917  0x45, 0x00, 0x00, 0x7d, 0xd8, 0xf3, 0x40, 0x00,
8918  0x40, 0x06, 0x63, 0x85, 0x7f, 0x00, 0x00, 0x01,
8919  0x7f, 0x00, 0x00, 0x01
8920  };
8921  uint8_t raw_tcp[] = {
8922  0xad, 0x22, 0x04, 0x00, 0x16, 0x39, 0x72,
8923  0xe2, 0x16, 0x1f, 0x79, 0x84, 0x80, 0x18,
8924  0x01, 0x01, 0xfe, 0x71, 0x00, 0x00, 0x01,
8925  0x01, 0x08, 0x0a, 0x00, 0x22, 0xaa, 0x10,
8926  0x00, 0x22, 0xaa, 0x10
8927  };
8928  uint8_t buf[] = {
8929  0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x08, 0x62, 0x6f, 0x6f, 0x65,
8930  0x65, 0x6b, 0x0d, 0x0a, 0x4c, 0x45, 0x4e, 0x31,
8931  0x20, 0x38, 0x0d, 0x0a, 0x66, 0x6f, 0x30, 0x30, /* LEN1|20| ends at 17 */
8932  0x30, 0x38, 0x0d, 0x0a, 0x4c, 0x45, 0x4e, 0x32, /* "0008" at offset 5 */
8933  0x20, 0x39, 0x39, 0x39, 0x39, 0x39, 0x39, 0x39,
8934  0x39, 0x39, 0x39, 0x39, 0x39, 0x39, 0x39, 0x39,
8935  0x39, 0x39, 0x39, 0x39, 0x39, 0x39, 0x39, 0x39,
8936  0x39, 0x39, 0x39, 0x0d, 0x0a, 0x41, 0x41, 0x41,
8937  0x41, 0x41, 0x41, 0x0d, 0x0a, 0x0d, 0x0a, 0x0d,
8938  0x0a
8939  };
8940  uint16_t ethlen = sizeof(raw_eth);
8941  uint16_t ipv4len = sizeof(raw_ipv4);
8942  uint16_t tcplen = sizeof(raw_tcp);
8943  uint16_t buflen = sizeof(buf);
8944 
8945  memset(&th_v, 0, sizeof(ThreadVars));
8946  memset(p1, 0, SIZE_OF_PACKET);
8947 
8948  /* Copy raw data into packet */
8949  if (PacketCopyData(p1, raw_eth, ethlen) == -1) {
8950  SCFree(p1);
8951  return 1;
8952  }
8953  if (PacketCopyDataOffset(p1, ethlen, raw_ipv4, ipv4len) == -1) {
8954  SCFree(p1);
8955  return 1;
8956  }
8957  if (PacketCopyDataOffset(p1, ethlen + ipv4len, raw_tcp, tcplen) == -1) {
8958  SCFree(p1);
8959  return 1;
8960  }
8961  if (PacketCopyDataOffset(p1, ethlen + ipv4len + tcplen, buf, buflen) == -1) {
8962  SCFree(p1);
8963  return 1;
8964  }
8965  SET_PKT_LEN(p1, ethlen + ipv4len + tcplen + buflen);
8966 
8967  PACKET_RESET_CHECKSUMS(p1);
8968  p1->ethh = (EthernetHdr *)raw_eth;
8969  p1->ip4h = (IPV4Hdr *)raw_ipv4;
8970  p1->tcph = (TCPHdr *)raw_tcp;
8971  p1->src.family = AF_INET;
8972  p1->dst.family = AF_INET;
8973  p1->payload = GET_PKT_DATA(p1) + ethlen + ipv4len + tcplen;
8974  p1->payload_len = buflen;
8975  p1->proto = IPPROTO_TCP;
8976 
8977  DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx = DetectEngineCtxInit();
8978  if (de_ctx == NULL) {
8979  goto end;
8980  }
8981 
8982  de_ctx->mpm_matcher = mpm_type;
8983  de_ctx->flags |= DE_QUIET;
8984 
8985  de_ctx->sig_list = SigInit(de_ctx,
8986  "alert tcp any any -> any any "
8987  "(content:\"LEN1|20|\"; "
8988  "byte_test:4,=,8,0; "
8989  "msg:\"byte_test keyword check(1)\"; sid:1;)");
8990  if (de_ctx->sig_list == NULL) {
8991  result &= 0;
8992  goto end;
8993  }
8994  de_ctx->sig_list->next = SigInit(de_ctx,
8995  "alert tcp any any -> any any "
8996  "(content:\"LEN1|20|\"; "
8997  "byte_test:4,=,8,5,relative,string,dec; "
8998  "msg:\"byte_test keyword check(2)\"; sid:2;)");
8999  if (de_ctx->sig_list->next == NULL) {
9000  result &= 0;
9001  goto end;
9002  }
9003 
9004  SigGroupBuild(de_ctx);
9005  DetectEngineThreadCtxInit(&th_v, (void *)de_ctx, (void *)&det_ctx);
9006 
9007  SigMatchSignatures(&th_v, de_ctx, det_ctx, p1);
9008  if (PacketAlertCheck(p1, 1)) {
9009  result = 1;
9010  } else {
9011  result = 0;
9012  printf("sid 1 didn't alert, but should have: ");
9013  goto cleanup;
9014  }
9015  if (PacketAlertCheck(p1, 2)) {
9016  result = 1;
9017  } else {
9018  result = 0;
9019  printf("sid 2 didn't alert, but should have: ");
9020  goto cleanup;
9021  }
9022 
9023 cleanup:
9024  SigGroupCleanup(de_ctx);
9025  SigCleanSignatures(de_ctx);
9026 
9027  if (det_ctx != NULL)
9028  DetectEngineThreadCtxDeinit(&th_v, (void *)det_ctx);
9029  DetectEngineCtxFree(de_ctx);
9030 
9031 end:
9032  SCFree(p1);
9033  return result;
9034 }

9484 /**
9485  * \test SigTest41NoPacketInspection is a test to check that when PKT_NOPACKET_INSPECTION
9486  * flag is set, we don't need to inspect the packet protocol header or its contents.
9487  */
9488 
9489 int SigTest40NoPacketInspection01(void)
9490 {
9491 
9492  uint8_t *buf = (uint8_t *)
9493  "220 (vsFTPd 2.0.5)\r\n";
9494  uint16_t buflen = strlen((char *)buf);
9495  Packet *p = SCMalloc(SIZE_OF_PACKET);
9496  TCPHdr tcphdr;
9497  if (unlikely(p == NULL))
9498  return 0;
9499  ThreadVars th_v;
9500  DetectEngineThreadCtx *det_ctx = NULL;
9501  PacketQueue pq;
9502  Flow f;
9503  int result = 0;
9504 
9505  memset(&th_v, 0, sizeof(th_v));
9506  memset(p, 0, SIZE_OF_PACKET);
9507  memset(&pq, 0, sizeof(pq));
9508  memset(&f, 0, sizeof(f));
9509  memset(&tcphdr, 0, sizeof(tcphdr));
9510 
9511  p->src.family = AF_INET;
9512  p->src.addr_data32[0] = UTHSetIPv4Address("192.168.0.1");
9513  p->dst.addr_data32[0] = UTHSetIPv4Address("1.2.3.4");
9514  p->dst.family = AF_INET;
9515  p->payload = buf;
9516  p->payload_len = buflen;
9517  p->proto = IPPROTO_TCP;
9518  p->dp = 34260;
9519  p->sp = 21;
9520  p->flowflags |= FLOW_PKT_TOSERVER;
9521  p->flags |= PKT_NOPACKET_INSPECTION;
9522  p->tcph = &tcphdr;
9523  p->flow = &f;
9524 
9525  FLOW_INITIALIZE(&f);
9526 
9527  DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx = DetectEngineCtxInit();
9528  if (de_ctx == NULL) {
9529  goto end;
9530  }
9531 
9532  de_ctx->flags |= DE_QUIET;
9533 
9534  de_ctx->sig_list = SigInit(de_ctx,"alert tcp any any -> 1.2.3.4 any (msg:\"No Packet Inspection Test\"; flow:to_server; sid:2; rev:1;)");
9535  if (de_ctx->sig_list == NULL) {
9536  result = 0;
9537  goto end;
9538  }
9539 
9540  SigGroupBuild(de_ctx);
9541  DetectEngineThreadCtxInit(&th_v, (void *)de_ctx,(void *)&det_ctx);
9542  det_ctx->de_ctx = de_ctx;
9543 
9544  Detect(&th_v, p, det_ctx, &pq, NULL);
9545  if (PacketAlertCheck(p, 2))
9546  result = 0;
9547  else
9548  result = 1;
9549 
9550  SigGroupCleanup(de_ctx);
9551  SigCleanSignatures(de_ctx);
9552  DetectEngineThreadCtxDeinit(&th_v, (void *)det_ctx);
9553  //PatternMatchDestroy(mpm_ctx);
9554  DetectEngineCtxFree(de_ctx);
9555 end:
9556  SCFree(p);
9557  return result;
9558 }

10525 static int SigTestContent01Real (int mpm_type)
10526 {
10527  uint8_t *buf = (uint8_t *)"01234567890123456789012345678901";
10528  uint16_t buflen = strlen((char *)buf);
10529  ThreadVars th_v;
10530  DetectEngineThreadCtx *det_ctx = NULL;
10531  int result = 0;
10532 
10533  memset(&th_v, 0, sizeof(th_v));
10534 
10535  Packet *p = NULL;
10536  p = UTHBuildPacket((uint8_t *)buf, buflen, IPPROTO_TCP);
10537 
10538  DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx = DetectEngineCtxInit();
10539  if (de_ctx == NULL) {
10540  goto end;
10541  }
10542 
10543  de_ctx->mpm_matcher = mpm_type;
10544  de_ctx->flags |= DE_QUIET;
10545 
10546  de_ctx->sig_list = SigInit(de_ctx,"alert tcp any any -> any any (msg:\"Test 32\"; content:\"01234567890123456789012345678901\"; sid:1;)");
10547  if (de_ctx->sig_list == NULL) {
10548  result = 0;
10549  goto end;
10550  }
10551 
10552  SigGroupBuild(de_ctx);
10553  DetectEngineThreadCtxInit(&th_v, (void *)de_ctx, (void *)&det_ctx);
10554 
10555  SigMatchSignatures(&th_v, de_ctx, det_ctx, p);
10556  if (PacketAlertCheck(p, 1))
10557  result = 1;
10558  else
10559  printf("sig 1 didn't match: ");
10560 
10561  SigGroupCleanup(de_ctx);
10562  SigCleanSignatures(de_ctx);
10563 
10564  DetectEngineThreadCtxDeinit(&th_v, (void *)det_ctx);
10565  DetectEngineCtxFree(de_ctx);
10566 end:
10567  UTHFreePackets(&p, 1);
10568  return result;
10569 }

11037  memset(p1, 0, SIZE_OF_PACKET);
11038  DecodeEthernet(&th_v, &dtv, p1, rawpkt1, sizeof(rawpkt1), NULL);
11039  SigMatchSignatures(&th_v, de_ctx, det_ctx, p1);
11040  if (!(PacketAlertCheck(p1, 556))) {
11041  printf("failed to match on packet 1: ");
11042  goto end;
11043  }
11044 
11045  /* packet 2 */
11046  p2 = SCMalloc(SIZE_OF_PACKET);
11047  if (unlikely(p2 == NULL))
11048  return 0;
11049  memset(p2, 0, SIZE_OF_PACKET);
11050  DecodeEthernet(&th_v, &dtv, p2, rawpkt2, sizeof(rawpkt2), NULL);
11051  SigMatchSignatures(&th_v, de_ctx, det_ctx, p2);
11052  if (!(PacketAlertCheck(p2, 556))) {
11053  printf("failed to match on packet 2: ");
11054  goto end;
11055  }
11056 
11057  /* packet 3 */
11058  p3 = SCMalloc(SIZE_OF_PACKET);
11059  if (unlikely(p3 == NULL))
11060  return 0;
11061  memset(p3, 0, SIZE_OF_PACKET);
11062  DecodeEthernet(&th_v, &dtv, p3, rawpkt3, sizeof(rawpkt3), NULL);
11063  SigMatchSignatures(&th_v, de_ctx, det_ctx, p3);
11064  if (!(PacketAlertCheck(p3, 556))) {
11065  printf("failed to match on packet 3: ");
11066  goto end;
11067  }
11068 
11069  /* packet 4 */
11070  p4 = SCMalloc(SIZE_OF_PACKET);
11071  if (unlikely(p4 == NULL))
11072  return 0;
11073  memset(p4, 0, SIZE_OF_PACKET);
11074  DecodeEthernet(&th_v, &dtv, p4, rawpkt4, sizeof(rawpkt4), NULL);
11075  SigMatchSignatures(&th_v, de_ctx, det_ctx, p4);
11076  if (!(PacketAlertCheck(p4, 556))) {
11077  printf("failed to match on packet 4: ");
11078  goto end;
11079  }
11080 
11081  /* packet 5 */
11082  uint8_t *p5buf = (uint8_t *)"Hi, this is a big test to check content matches";
11083  uint16_t p5buflen = strlen((char *)p5buf);
11084  Packet *p5 = UTHBuildPacket(p5buf, p5buflen, IPPROTO_TCP);
11085  SigMatchSignatures(&th_v, de_ctx, det_ctx, p5);
11086  if (!(PacketAlertCheck(p5, 556))) {
11087  printf("failed to match on packet 5: ");
11088  goto end;
11089  }
11090  UTHFreePackets(&p5, 1);
11091 
11092  result = 1;
11093 end:
11094  if (de_ctx != NULL) {
11095  SigGroupCleanup(de_ctx);
11096  SigCleanSignatures(de_ctx);
11097  }
11098 
11099  if (det_ctx != NULL)
11100  DetectEngineThreadCtxDeinit(&th_v, (void *)det_ctx);
11101 
11102  if (de_ctx != NULL)
11103  DetectEngineCtxFree(de_ctx);
11104 
11105  if (p1 != NULL) {
11106  PACKET_RECYCLE(p1);
11107  SCFree(p1);
11108  }
11109  if (p2 != NULL) {
11110  PACKET_RECYCLE(p2);
11111  SCFree(p2);
11112  }
11113  if (p3 != NULL) {
11114  PACKET_RECYCLE(p3);
11115  SCFree(p3);
11116  }
11117  if (p4 != NULL) {
11118  PACKET_RECYCLE(p4);
11119  SCFree(p4);
11120  }
11121  FlowShutdown();
11122  return result;
11123 }

11317  goto end;

11324  printf("sig 1 didn't alert, but it should: ");
11325  goto end;
11326  }
11327 
11328  if ( !(p->flow->flags & FLOW_ACTION_DROP)) {
11329  printf("sig 1 alerted but flow was not flagged correctly: ");
11330  goto end;
11331  }
11332 
11333  /* Ok, now we know that the flag is set for proto http */
11334 
11335  result = 1;
11336 
11337 end:

11339  AppLayerParserThreadCtxFree(alp_tctx);
11340  if (det_ctx != NULL)
11341  DetectEngineThreadCtxDeinit(&tv, det_ctx);
11342  if (de_ctx != NULL)
11343  SigGroupCleanup(de_ctx);
11344  if (de_ctx != NULL)
11345  DetectEngineCtxFree(de_ctx);
11346 
11347  StreamTcpFreeConfig(TRUE);
11348  FLOW_DESTROY(&f);
11349 
11350  UTHFreePackets(&p, 1);
11351  return result;
11352 }

11458 /** \test test if the engine set flag to drop pkts of a flow that
11459  * triggered a drop action on IPS mode, and it doesn't inspect
11460  * any other packet of the stream */
11461 static int SigTestDropFlow03(void)
11462 {
11463  int result = 0;
11464  Flow f;
11465  HtpState *http_state = NULL;
11466  uint8_t http_buf1[] = "POST /one HTTP/1.0\r\n"
11467  "User-Agent: Mozilla/1.0\r\n"
11468  "Cookie: hellocatch\r\n\r\n";
11469  uint32_t http_buf1_len = sizeof(http_buf1) - 1;
11470 
11471  uint8_t http_buf2[] = "POST /two HTTP/1.0\r\n"
11472  "User-Agent: Mozilla/1.0\r\n"
11473  "Cookie: hellocatch\r\n\r\n";
11474  uint32_t http_buf2_len = sizeof(http_buf1) - 1;
11475 
11476  /* Set the engine mode to IPS */
11477  EngineModeSetIPS();
11478 
11479  TcpSession ssn;
11480  Packet *p1 = NULL;
11481  Packet *p2 = NULL;
11482  Signature *s = NULL;
11483  ThreadVars tv;
11484  DetectEngineThreadCtx *det_ctx = NULL;
11485  AppLayerParserThreadCtx *alp_tctx = AppLayerParserThreadCtxAlloc();
11486 
11487  memset(&tv, 0, sizeof(ThreadVars));
11488  memset(&f, 0, sizeof(Flow));
11489  memset(&ssn, 0, sizeof(TcpSession));
11490 
11491  p1 = UTHBuildPacket(NULL, 0, IPPROTO_TCP);
11492  p2 = UTHBuildPacket(NULL, 0, IPPROTO_TCP);
11493 
11494  FLOW_INITIALIZE(&f);
11495  f.protoctx = (void *)&ssn;
11496  f.proto = IPPROTO_TCP;
11497  f.flags |= FLOW_IPV4;
11498 
11499  p1->flow = &f;
11500  p1->flowflags |= FLOW_PKT_TOSERVER;
11501  p1->flowflags |= FLOW_PKT_ESTABLISHED;
11502  p1->flags |= PKT_HAS_FLOW|PKT_STREAM_EST;
11503 
11504  p2->flow = &f;
11505  p2->flowflags |= FLOW_PKT_TOSERVER;
11506  p2->flowflags |= FLOW_PKT_ESTABLISHED;
11507  p2->flags |= PKT_HAS_FLOW|PKT_STREAM_EST;
11508  f.alproto = ALPROTO_HTTP;
11509 
11510  StreamTcpInitConfig(TRUE);
11511 
11512  DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx = DetectEngineCtxInit();
11513  if (de_ctx == NULL) {
11514  goto end;
11515  }
11516 
11517  de_ctx->mpm_matcher = MPM_B2G;
11518  de_ctx->flags |= DE_QUIET;
11519 
11520  s = de_ctx->sig_list = SigInit(de_ctx, "drop tcp any any -> any 80 "
11521  "(msg:\"Test proto match\"; uricontent:\"one\";"
11522  "sid:1;)");
11523  if (s == NULL) {
11524  goto end;
11525  }
11526 
11527  /* the no inspection flag should be set after the first sig gets triggered,
11528  * so the second packet should not match the next sig (because of no inspection) */
11529  s = de_ctx->sig_list->next = SigInit(de_ctx, "alert tcp any any -> any 80 "
11530  "(msg:\"Test proto match\"; uricontent:\"two\";"
11531  "sid:2;)");
11532  if (s == NULL) {
11533  goto end;
11534  }
11535 
11536  SigGroupBuild(de_ctx);
11537  DetectEngineThreadCtxInit(&tv, (void *)de_ctx, (void *)&det_ctx);
11538 
11539  SCMutexLock(&f.m);
11540  int r = AppLayerParserParse(alp_tctx, &f, ALPROTO_HTTP, STREAM_TOSERVER, http_buf1, http_buf1_len);
11541  if (r != 0) {
11542  printf("toserver chunk 1 returned %" PRId32 ", expected 0: ", r);
11543  SCMutexUnlock(&f.m);
11544  goto end;
11545  }
11546  SCMutexUnlock(&f.m);
11547 
11548  http_state = f.alstate;
11549  if (http_state == NULL) {
11550  printf("no http state: ");
11551  goto end;
11552  }
11553 
11554  /* do detect */
11555  SigMatchSignatures(&tv, de_ctx, det_ctx, p1);
11556 
11557  if (!PacketAlertCheck(p1, 1)) {
11558  printf("sig 1 didn't alert on p1, but it should: ");
11559  goto end;
11560  }
11561 
11562  if ( !(p1->flow->flags & FLOW_ACTION_DROP)) {
11563  printf("sig 1 alerted but flow was not flagged correctly: ");
11564  goto end;
11565  }
11566 
11567  /* Second part.. Let's feed with another packet */
11568  if (StreamTcpCheckFlowDrops(p2) == 1) {
11569  SCLogDebug("This flow/stream triggered a drop rule");
11570  FlowSetNoPacketInspectionFlag(p2->flow);
11571  DecodeSetNoPacketInspectionFlag(p2);
11572  StreamTcpDisableAppLayer(p2->flow);
11573  p2->action |= ACTION_DROP;
11574  /* return the segments to the pool */
11575  StreamTcpSessionPktFree(p2);
11576  }
11577 
11578 
11579  if ( !(p2->flags & PKT_NOPACKET_INSPECTION)) {
11580  printf("The packet was not flagged with no-inspection: ");
11581  goto end;
11582  }
11583 
11584  SCMutexLock(&f.m);
11585  r = AppLayerParserParse(alp_tctx, &f, ALPROTO_HTTP, STREAM_TOSERVER, http_buf2, http_buf2_len);
11586  if (r != 0) {
11587  printf("toserver chunk 2 returned %" PRId32 ", expected 0: ", r);
11588  SCMutexUnlock(&f.m);
11589  goto end;
11590  }
11591  SCMutexUnlock(&f.m);
11592 
11593  /* do detect */
11594  SigMatchSignatures(&tv, de_ctx, det_ctx, p2);
11595 
11596  if (PacketAlertCheck(p2, 1)) {
11597  printf("sig 1 alerted, but it should not since the no pkt inspection should be set: ");
11598  goto end;
11599  }
11600 
11601  if (PacketAlertCheck(p2, 2)) {
11602  printf("sig 2 alerted, but it should not since the no pkt inspection should be set: ");
11603  goto end;
11604  }
11605 
11606  if ( !(PACKET_TEST_ACTION(p2, ACTION_DROP))) {
11607  printf("A \"drop\" action should be set from the flow to the packet: ");
11608  goto end;
11609  }
11610 
11611  result = 1;
11612 
11613 end:
11614  if (alp_tctx != NULL)
11615  AppLayerParserThreadCtxFree(alp_tctx);
11616  if (det_ctx != NULL)
11617  DetectEngineThreadCtxDeinit(&tv, det_ctx);
11618  if (de_ctx != NULL)
11619  SigGroupCleanup(de_ctx);
11620  if (de_ctx != NULL)
11621  DetectEngineCtxFree(de_ctx);
11622 
11623  StreamTcpFreeConfig(TRUE);
11624  FLOW_DESTROY(&f);
11625 
11626  UTHFreePackets(&p1, 1);
11627  UTHFreePackets(&p2, 1);
11628 
11629  /* Restore mode to IDS */
11630  EngineModeSetIDS();
11631  return result;
11632 }

11634 /** \test test if the engine set flag to drop pkts of a flow that
11635  * triggered a drop action on IDS mode, but continue the inspection
11636  * as usual (instead of on IPS mode) */
11637 static int SigTestDropFlow04(void)
11638 {
11639  int result = 0;
11640  Flow f;
11641  HtpState *http_state = NULL;
11642  uint8_t http_buf1[] = "POST /one HTTP/1.0\r\n"
11643  "User-Agent: Mozilla/1.0\r\n"
11644  "Cookie: hellocatch\r\n\r\n";
11645  uint32_t http_buf1_len = sizeof(http_buf1) - 1;
11646 
11647  uint8_t http_buf2[] = "POST /two HTTP/1.0\r\n"
11648  "User-Agent: Mozilla/1.0\r\n"
11649  "Cookie: hellocatch\r\n\r\n";
11650  uint32_t http_buf2_len = sizeof(http_buf1) - 1;
11651 
11652  TcpSession ssn;
11653  Packet *p1 = NULL;
11654  Packet *p2 = NULL;
11655  Signature *s = NULL;
11656  ThreadVars tv;
11657  DetectEngineThreadCtx *det_ctx = NULL;
11658  AppLayerParserThreadCtx *alp_tctx = AppLayerParserThreadCtxAlloc();
11659 
11660  memset(&tv, 0, sizeof(ThreadVars));
11661  memset(&f, 0, sizeof(Flow));
11662  memset(&ssn, 0, sizeof(TcpSession));
11663 
11664  p1 = UTHBuildPacket(NULL, 0, IPPROTO_TCP);
11665  p2 = UTHBuildPacket(NULL, 0, IPPROTO_TCP);
11666 
11667  FLOW_INITIALIZE(&f);
11668  f.protoctx = (void *)&ssn;
11669  f.proto = IPPROTO_TCP;
11670  f.flags |= FLOW_IPV4;
11671 
11672  p1->flow = &f;
11673  p1->flowflags |= FLOW_PKT_TOSERVER;
11674  p1->flowflags |= FLOW_PKT_ESTABLISHED;
11675  p1->flags |= PKT_HAS_FLOW|PKT_STREAM_EST;
11676 
11677  p2->flow = &f;
11678  p2->flowflags |= FLOW_PKT_TOSERVER;
11679  p2->flowflags |= FLOW_PKT_ESTABLISHED;
11680  p2->flags |= PKT_HAS_FLOW|PKT_STREAM_EST;
11681  f.alproto = ALPROTO_HTTP;
11682 
11683  StreamTcpInitConfig(TRUE);
11684 
11685  DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx = DetectEngineCtxInit();
11686  if (de_ctx == NULL) {
11687  goto end;
11688  }
11689  de_ctx->mpm_matcher = MPM_B2G;
11690  de_ctx->flags |= DE_QUIET;
11691 
11692  s = de_ctx->sig_list = SigInit(de_ctx, "drop tcp any any -> any 80 "
11693  "(msg:\"Test proto match\"; uricontent:\"one\";"
11694  "sid:1;)");
11695  if (s == NULL) {
11696  goto end;
11697  }
11698 
11699  /* the no inspection flag should be set after the first sig gets triggered,
11700  * so the second packet should not match the next sig (because of no inspection) */
11701  s = de_ctx->sig_list->next = SigInit(de_ctx, "alert tcp any any -> any 80 "
11702  "(msg:\"Test proto match\"; uricontent:\"two\";"
11703  "sid:2;)");
11704  if (s == NULL) {
11705  goto end;
11706  }
11707 
11708  SigGroupBuild(de_ctx);
11709  DetectEngineThreadCtxInit(&tv, (void *)de_ctx, (void *)&det_ctx);
11710 
11711  SCMutexLock(&f.m);
11712  int r = AppLayerParserParse(alp_tctx, &f, ALPROTO_HTTP, STREAM_TOSERVER, http_buf1, http_buf1_len);
11713  if (r != 0) {
11714  printf("toserver chunk 1 returned %" PRId32 ", expected 0: ", r);
11715  SCMutexUnlock(&f.m);
11716  goto end;
11717  }
11718  SCMutexUnlock(&f.m);
11719 
11720  http_state = f.alstate;
11721  if (http_state == NULL) {
11722  printf("no http state: ");
11723  goto end;
11724  }
11725 
11726  /* do detect */
11727  SigMatchSignatures(&tv, de_ctx, det_ctx, p1);
11728 
11729  if (!PacketAlertCheck(p1, 1)) {
11730  printf("sig 1 didn't alert on p1, but it should: ");
11731  goto end;
11732  }
11733 
11734  if (PacketAlertCheck(p1, 2)) {
11735  printf("sig 2 alerted on p1, but it should not: ");
11736  goto end;
11737  }
11738 
11739  if ( !(p1->flow->flags & FLOW_ACTION_DROP)) {
11740  printf("sig 1 alerted but flow was not flagged correctly: ");
11741  goto end;
11742  }
11743 
11744  if (!(PACKET_TEST_ACTION(p1, ACTION_DROP))) {
11745  printf("A \"drop\" action was set from the flow to the packet "
11746  "which is right, but setting the flag shouldn't disable "
11747  "inspection on the packet in IDS mode");
11748  goto end;
11749  }
11750 
11751  /* Second part.. Let's feed with another packet */
11752  if (StreamTcpCheckFlowDrops(p2) == 1) {
11753  FlowSetNoPacketInspectionFlag(p2->flow);
11754  DecodeSetNoPacketInspectionFlag(p2);
11755  StreamTcpDisableAppLayer(p2->flow);
11756  p2->action |= ACTION_DROP;
11757  /* return the segments to the pool */
11758  StreamTcpSessionPktFree(p2);
11759  }
11760 
11761  if ( (p2->flags & PKT_NOPACKET_INSPECTION)) {
11762  printf("The packet was flagged with no-inspection but we are not on IPS mode: ");
11763  goto end;
11764  }
11765 
11766  SCMutexLock(&f.m);
11767  r = AppLayerParserParse(alp_tctx, &f, ALPROTO_HTTP, STREAM_TOSERVER, http_buf2, http_buf2_len);
11768  if (r != 0) {
11769  printf("toserver chunk 2 returned %" PRId32 ", expected 0: ", r);
11770  SCMutexUnlock(&f.m);
11771  goto end;
11772  }
11773  SCMutexUnlock(&f.m);
11774 
11775  /* do detect */
11776  SigMatchSignatures(&tv, de_ctx, det_ctx, p2);
11777 
11778  if (PacketAlertCheck(p2, 1)) {
11779  printf("sig 1 alerted, but it should not: ");
11780  goto end;
11781  }
11782 
11783  if (!PacketAlertCheck(p2, 2)) {
11784  printf("sig 2 didn't alert, but it should, since we are not on IPS mode: ");
11785  goto end;
11786  }
11787 
11788  if (!(PACKET_TEST_ACTION(p2, ACTION_DROP))) {
11789  printf("A \"drop\" action was set from the flow to the packet "
11790  "which is right, but setting the flag shouldn't disable "
11791  "inspection on the packet in IDS mode");
11792  goto end;
11793  }
11794 
11795  result = 1;
11796 
11797 end:
11798  if (alp_tctx != NULL)
11799  AppLayerParserThreadCtxFree(alp_tctx);
11800  if (det_ctx != NULL)
11801  DetectEngineThreadCtxDeinit(&tv, det_ctx);
11802  if (de_ctx != NULL)
11803  SigGroupCleanup(de_ctx);
11804  if (de_ctx != NULL)
11805  DetectEngineCtxFree(de_ctx);
11806 
11807  StreamTcpFreeConfig(TRUE);
11808  FLOW_DESTROY(&f);
11809 
11810  UTHFreePackets(&p1, 1);
11811  UTHFreePackets(&p2, 1);
11812 
11813  return result;
11814 }
